title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and pepper.
Layer broccoli and chicken soup mixture in greased casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper. Saute until garlic is golden. Add steak to this. Brown lightly. Remove meat. Add green peppers and onions.
Cook approximately 3 to 5 minutes. Return beef to skillet.
Add soy sauce, sugar, bouillon and water chestnuts. Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to skillet along with green onions. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over rice.
May use wok in place of skillet.

title: chewy-o's bars
directions: Melt butter and spread over bottom of jelly roll pan. Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over butter.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and cereal.
Pour milk over bars evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While warm run knife around edge of pan to loosen sides.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: play dough recipe #2
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Add oil and water gradually to the mixture.
Knead as your would knead dough until the mixture is smooth and easy to handle.
Add more flour as needed as the child plays with it.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash and oil potatoes.
Wrap with alumniunum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 - 1/2 hours, or until soft.
Cut in halves.
Spoon out potato.
Leave hull in tact.
In lg. bowl, add milk, butter, salt, pepper to potato.
Mix to mashed potato consistency.
Spoon potato mix back into hull.
Add broccoli on top; add crumbled bacon, and then cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: chicken curry
directions: Heat oil and butter in a medium size frying pan; saute the onions, garlic and chopped ginger about 2 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Stir in the rest of the spices; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil or butter in a large frying pan; brown chicken on all sides, a few pieces at a time. Return all the chicken to the pan; spoon the onion mixture over the chicken.
Add the tomatoes.
Cover and simmer gently for about 1 hour or until chicken is just tender; do not overcook.
Serve with steamed rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until done; drain.
Mix soups, enchilada sauce, olives, chilies and milk with the hamburger and onions.
Tear up 5 or 6 corn tortillas; put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour on half the sauce.
Repeat layer of tortillas and the remaining sauce.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt the caramels with the Pet milk and pecans. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin together, then dip caramels.

title: stir-fry beef with asparagus
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut flank steak across the grain into very thin slices. Blend soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and corn starch. Pour over sliced beef; stir to coat. Bias cut asparagus into 1 inch pieces. Drop into boiling water 1 to 2 minutes; drain. Heat wok or skillet with 3 tablespoons oil. When sizzling, add 1 teaspoon sugar. Add beef; cook and stir 1 minute. Add asparagus; cook and stir 1 minute longer. Add sherry and chicken broth. Cook 1/2 minute longer. Serve over hot rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour can of peaches or whatever you prefer into a loaf pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 box of cake mix over peaches.
Slice butter to cover cake mix.
Bake approximately 35 minutes, depending on your oven.
Top should be golden brown.

title: summer salsa
directions: In hot water bath submerge tomatoes in boiling water to loosen skins.
Remove and discard skins.
Chop all vegetables into small, bite-size pieces.
Simmer in large pot for 10 minutes.
Put in warm jars with lids.
Place in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken and vegetables, spreading mixture evenly in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter, corn flakes and parsley flakes and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly, store in airtight containers.
Add hot water and serve.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat in hot fat; add soy sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add celery and onion; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture.
Add chestnuts, bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Heat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: candied yams
directions: Mix all ingredients except yams.
Cook until clear.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Mix until coarse crumbs form. Stir in water, egg and vinegar. Divide into 3 balls. Freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon.
Mix vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar in a separate bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Start preparing to boil linguine as directed on box.
While linguine is cooking, start sauce.
Brown the garlic in a pan with olive oil.
Garlic should be chopped or left whole.
Garlic should be done to golden brown.
Add clams with juice and cook until linguine is done.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour over drained linguine and serve.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Mix together.
Chill, roll and flatten into small pieces, using wax paper.
Serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into large chunks.
Put in large pot with 1 tsp. salt and water to cover.
Cook until fork tender.
Drain. Set aside to cool.
When cool enough to handle, use a dull knife to cut into very small pieces, some will be almost a mashed consistency.
Put into a large bowl.
Add onion, celery, green onion, eggs, and relish.
In a dish mix together mustard, miracle whip, 1/2 tsp. salt and pepper.
Taste before you add it to potato mixture.
Adjust mustard to personal preference.
Mix into potatoes until completely blended.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving, but preferable over night.

title: to die for pot roast
directions: Choose a pot roast big enough to fit in your slow cooker. Place roast in cooker. Mix envelopes of dry mix together in a small bowl. Mix well. Pour mixes over roast. Cover. Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours, depending on size of pot roast.

title: sesame broccoli stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Stir in chili sauce and sesame oil and set aside.

title: deluxe macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, pepper and cheese.
Add macaroni and stir well. Pour in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Combine in a large bowl the melted butter (or margarine), brown and white sugars, eggs and vanilla. Mix well, then add 2 cups flour, baking soda and baking powder. Stir in oats, corn flakes, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. With ice cream scoop 3/4 full, place dough on ungreased baking sheet, 1 to 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Cool on paper towels. Makes 18 extra large cookies.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix together; save 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Press the rest on bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: Bring water, shortening and cocoa to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture; mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
After cake has baked 15 minutes, start frosting.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Bake on 425° for 45 minutes.
Last 10 minutes brush with sugar water.
Ovens vary, may have to turn down to 400°.

title: kimmy's "secret stuffed shrimp"
directions: Saute onions, peppers, garlic and celery.
Puree scallops with the sauteed veggies (use food processor).
Mix ingredients together (except crackers).
Add Ritz crackers until you have a nice consistency (not too dry and not too moist).

title: corn dog batter
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat in egg.
Add milk.
Dip wieners in batter and fry.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook and stir onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Cook, uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or at 375° for 1 hour.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Remove broccoli flowerets from stalk and wash thoroughly; drain and dry on paper towels (do not cook).
Mix all other ingredients and shake well.
Pour over broccoli and marinate 24 hours.
Turn broccoli several times.
Drain before serving.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Drain clam juice into frying pan.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add butter, parsley, oregano, garlic, Tabasco sauce and then clams and bread crumbs.
Remove from heat and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix just a little bit.
Coat with paprika.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, milk and egg.
Add cracker crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Pour into greased casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch for 50
directions: Add Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar to hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and pineapple juice; chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale and 7-Up.

title: prune pudding
directions: Pit and chop the prunes.
Blend the reserved 1/2 cup prune juice with the cornstarch until smooth.
Combine prunes, sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch mixture in a saucepan.
Simmer until thick and clear.
Cool slightly.
Add nuts and cinnamon.
Chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Melt butter; add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Cook, covered, until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add flour.
Continue cooking with cover on for 15 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cook approximately 15 minutes, stirring frequently, to prevent sticking.
Add half and half, Velveeta (save some), jalapeno relish, minced garlic, salt and pepper (red and black) to taste. Cook on low heat approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add beer and mix well, approximately 25 strokes.
Pour in buttered bread pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
This bread will be heavy.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Simmer together over low heat approximately 4 hours.

title: jiggs dinner - newfoundland
directions: Soak meat in cold water overnight.
Drain meat and place in a large pot.
Tie peas in a cloth bag, leaving room for expansion and put in pot with beef.
Cover beef and peas with water.
Heat to boiling and cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Prepare vegetables, small carrots and potatoes may be left whole.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, adding cabbage last.
Remove peas from bag, place in bowl and mash with butter, salt and pepper to form "pease pudding."
Remove meat and cut into bite size pieces.
Arrange meat and vegetables on platter.
Serve the "pease pudding" in a separate bowl.
Newfoundlanders often pour the pot liquor (stock) over their dinner.

title: king kamehameha pie
directions: Combine 1 cup of the pineapple juice and the sugar.
Bring to boil; add apples.
Simmer, covered, until tender but not soft, 3 to 4 minutes.
Lift apples from syrup; set aside to drain. Combine cornstarch and remaining pineapple juice; add to syrup in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and salt.
Cool 10 minutes without stirring.
Pour about half into shell.
Arrange apples on top.
Put remaining syrup over apples.
Cool or chill. Garnish center with whipped cream or sour cream.
Sprinkle with chopped Macadamia nuts if desired.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise salad
directions: Pour gelatin into boiling water.
When granules are dissolved, set mixture aside to cool.
Add crushed bananas, thawed berries and chopped pecans to cooled mixture.
Pour one half of this into baking dish and place in refrigerator to set.
Spread sour cream over the top of congealed gelatin and pour remaining mixture of gelatin on top of sour cream.
Return to refrigerator until top part is congealed.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: magic cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll each marshmallow in melted margarine, then in cinnamon/sugar mixture. Wrap each coated marshmallow with a crescent triangle. Pinch edges together.
Dip in melted margarine and then in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until light brown.
(Marshmallows disappear during baking.)
Makes 8.

title: bread cube casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's sugared pecans
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add pecans to egg white mixture. Put pecans and egg white mixture into the pan of melted butter. Bake in a 300° oven, stirring every 5 to 8 minutes.
Bake until browned well.
Turn out and spread on aluminum foil to cool.
When completely cold, put in container or plastic bag.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, then orange juice.
Add flour that has been sifted with soda and cinnamon.
Fold in fruit that has been dusted with a small amount of flour.
Drop cookies onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oleo, in large bowl, mixing until fluffy.
Pour into raw pie shell.
Dribble oleo over entire surface of pie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes, until crust is golden brown and pie is congealed.

title: rock fish casserole
directions: Steam fish, remove all skin (I baked mine).
Combine fish, parsley and mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper and Old Bay.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter, add.
Blend flour and milk; let thicken and add to fish.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake until the crumbs get nice and brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Layer Tater Tots and ground beef.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over Tater Tots and beef.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: summer day squash
directions: Wash, dry and remove ends.
Split in half length ways.
Place in shallow microwaveable dish.
Make several slits in cut side of squash, spread margarine on and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook on high power for 3 minutes.
Should be tender enough for fork to pierce easily.
More cooking time may be required. Recheck for tenderness after 1 minute.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Mix at medium speed until thoroughly combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place margarine in hot skillet. Brown 1/2 cup sugar in skillet while cooking 2 cups sugar and milk in saucepan. Add sugar to milk mixture when it is brown. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.

title: corn pudding
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for two hours.
(This makes a very large amount.
You can cut it in half.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Boil noodles; drain.
Add soup and sour cream to meat mixture.
Serve noodles separately with hamburger mixture.

title: mississippi mud cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; bring to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Then add cocoa, vanilla and oats.
Stir well; drop onto waxed paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In large pan stir together first 3 ingredients.
Bring to rapid boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O. When Jell-O is completely dissolved, fold in strawberries making sure all berries are coated.
Cool overnight.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Hand mix the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into mixed ingredients.
Gradually add buttermilk into mixture until you have a stiff dough.
Add optional ingredients if you desire.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly and brush with buttermilk. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Cook pineapple and juice for 3 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O and let cool.
Then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 1 hour in an angel cake pan.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour in a baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: hot stuffed olives
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, salt, baking powder and paprika.
Roll out.
Wrap 1 teaspoon cheese dough around the olive and roll like a ball.
Put in freezer and when you want to serve, take right from freezer and put them in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese ball looks toasty in color.

title: hearty soup
directions: Brown beef with salt and onion.
Brown and drain sausage.
Add 2 cups water to the meat and cook vegetables in same pan.
Add seasoning as desired.
Add tomatoes and more water as needed. Substitute macaroni for potatoes, if desired.

title: peachy barbecue ribs
directions: Dice peaches.
Using juice of peaches, mix peaches, marmalade and barbecue sauce.
Place ribs in large pan or dish.
Pour mixture over ribs.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: polish stuffed cabbage
directions: In large pot, boil water.
Cut into core of cabbage.
Place whole cabbage in boiling water.
Separate leaves from cabbage; let cool.
Mix beef, veal and pork together.
Add rice, eggs, salt and pepper.
Place spoonful of meat mixture in center of cabbage; fold bottom, then side over, then top.
Place in lasagna dish with bacon strips on bottom.
Arrange cabbage in dish.
Top with soup and brown sugar.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, wine vinegar, onion and celery seed together and add to vegetables.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour separately, seven times each.
Set aside. Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, but still moist.
Lightly fold sugar into egg whites. Carefully fold in flour.
Add almond and vanilla extracts.
Spoon batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Invert.
Cool 1 hour.
Turn out onto cake platter.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Put hamburger in bowl.	Put
onion
in a separate bowl. Warm one tortilla at a time.
When warm, put big spoonful each of hamburger and onion and roll up.
Put in oblong baking pan. When all tortillas are
done, melt cheese, Milnot, chilies and pimentos.
Pour over tortillas; cover and put in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and
cook
minutes more until lightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull meat from bones.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Add other ingredients to spaghetti.
Bake long enough to heat through.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Peel and cut cucumbers into sticks.
Scrape all seeds out good. Soak in lime water overnight.
Wash thoroughly (several washings). Soak in cold water 3 hours.

title: never fail gingerbread
directions: Combine sugar, molasses and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with water, beating until smooth.
Bake in greased 6 x 10-inch pan in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken and tortillas
directions: Fry onions in small amount of fat until brown.
Add soup, green chilies, chicken and 1 soup can of water.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Line a casserole with corn tortillas.
Spoon chicken mixture over tortillas until covered.
Add a layer of cheese, tortillas and chicken mixture, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain lima beans and broccoli. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Put in a casserole bowl. Crush 2 1/2 cups Rice Chex and sprinkle on top. Melt 1 stick of butter. Pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: salsa(canned or fresh)
directions: Amounts of the ingredients depend on portion needed.
Cook down tomatoes, adding the rest of ingredients.
Use tomato paste if wanted.
After mixture has simmered and before salsa is ready to be served or canned, add white vinegar a little at a time, tasting after each addition.
The vinegar is the ingredient that seasons the salsa.
When reached desired taste, cool and serve. If canning, pour hot salsa into clean jars and hot water bath jars for 15 minutes.

title: quick ground beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown beef.
Add onion, salt and pepper while meat is browning.
Drain off excess fat.
Add soup and sour cream.
Simmer until heated through.
Add hot noodles.

title: baked chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix soup, parsley, onion and milk.
Dip chicken pieces in soup mixture; roll in stuffing mix and place in shallow baking pan (they can overlap).
Pour remaining soup around edges and between rows.
Sprinkle on any extra stuffing mix.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Saute onions and butter in skillet.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes and reduce heat to low. If too thick, use more milk until desired thickness.
For cheesier flavor, add 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
This recipe can be doubled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Squeeze out all the juice from the artichoke pieces and mix with remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 3-cup shallow baking dish (one that the spread can be served in). Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Serve hot with Triscuits, Melba toast or other round crackers.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients into crumbs and reserve 1/2 cup. Add egg, buttermilk and baking soda and dissolve in mixture.
Add vanilla; pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Crush Heath bars and add nuts and reserved crumbs; pour over cake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Crumble and brown beef in skillet; drain all fat.
Add onion; cook until almost tender.
Add tomatoes, seasoning and kidney beans.
Add bean liquid and water, a little bit at a time, to keep consistency of thick soup.
Remove bay leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and pour off grease.
Add 4 ounces tomato paste, onions and bell pepper.
Cook until onions are soft.
Mix in 3 eggs, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup cheese.

title: hi ho cookies
directions: Cook dates and milk in double boiler until thickened.
Add nuts.
Spread on Hi Ho crackers.
Bake eight minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces. Cook until crisp. Remove from pan.
In bacon grease, cook the garlic and onion until they smell good. Add the carrots and cabbage; stir-fry.
Pour mixture over rice. Crumble bacon on top. Add a little soy sauce to taste.

title: chile con queso(diabetic recipe)
directions: Microwave Velveeta and tomatoes and green chilies in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or green, red or yellow pepper wedges or other raw vegetables.
Microwave cooking time:
5 minutes.

title: cinnamon-orange rolls
directions: Unroll bread sticks on wax paper.
Slightly flatten.
Brush with margarine.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough. Press raisins or nuts into dough.
Roll up each piece jelly roll style.
Seal and place on greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Ice while warm.

title: little italy in a pot
directions: Brown meats in hot salad oil.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms. Blend.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add wine.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in 2/3 margarine until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with water and mix into a ball. Drain peaches.
Reserve 1/2 cup of syrup.
Combine sugar, flour and spices.
Add peaches, syrup and lemon juice. Mix.

title: jim's plain fajita
directions: Run each fajita slab through meat grinder or tenderizer.
Trim fat and skin, leaving some for flavor and to hold meat together. Generously sprinkle Adolph's tenderizer on both sides.
Set aside for 1 hour.
When coals are ready, place meat on grill.
Cook well done.
Slice across grain and serve with flour tortilla, hot sauce or pico de gallo.

title: tasty italian chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Place in bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over and let set overnight.
Place in pan or baking dish. Cover with foil.
Cook in oven until chicken is tender. During the cooking, turn and check the chicken for tenderness.

title: crouton crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers in a large Ziploc bag; mix well.
Add crackers and shake until crackers are coated.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Store in airtight container.
Use as croutons for salads or just as a snack.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Make jello as directed.
Let jello partly congeal.
Add fruit. Prepare lemon pudding as directed.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding. Spread over thickened jello.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Boil for 7 minutes over boiling water and beat.

title: dare's family favorite
directions: Drain asparagus and put in casserole.
Add 1/2 can of onions. Pour mushroom soup in.
Heat for 7 minutes on High in microwave. Add rest of onions on top; cook for 2 minutes more.

title: seafood tartlets
directions: Tart Shells:
Roll each slice of bread 1/4-inch thick.
Use a daisy cookie cutter to cut out tarts.
Lightly brush each tart with oleo.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: light and yummy chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk, pudding, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into shell and chill.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly, until well blended.
Divide into parts and add food coloring to each part.

title: gloria's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Bone chicken and remove skin.
Break into small pieces.
Grease bottom of casserole dish with butter.
Mix soup and milk until smooth and pour into dish.
Cover entire area with chicken.

title: grandmother's cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add beaten egg and milk to make a stiff batter.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve while hot.

title: pumpkin cream cheese custard
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add egg and mix well again.
Spread in pie shell.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Make white sauce. Add potatoes, ham and frozen peas. Place grated cheese on top. Heat in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tortillas.
Layer mixture with corn tortillas.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and all is hot throughout.

title: crabmeat spread "pizza"
directions: Mix first six ingredients and spread on a flat dish.
Make the outside edge higher, like the edge of a pizza crust.
Spread cocktail sauce over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle crab over cocktail sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: holly christmas cookies
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients on low heat.
Mix corn flakes.
Drop on waxed paper and decorate with red hots.

title: german casserole
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; drain, then add milk and cream cheese until it melts.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea syrup(makes 8 to 10 gallons of tea)
directions: Bring water and tea bags to a complete boil.
Turn heat to low; simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove bags.
Pour into gallon pitcher.
Slowly stir in 5 pounds sugar while tea is hot; stir very well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Combine all ingredients except dressing crumbs.
Top with 1/2 package herb dressing crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and browned.

title: cathy's fruit stuff
directions: Mix all the above together. The peach pie filling keeps the bananas from turning dark. It's really great for holidays. Use it on pound cakes, ice cream or just as a fruit salad.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Remove crust from bread; cut bread into cubes.
Combine bread cubes, eggs and milk in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in meat mixture and shape into 6 individual loaves.
Roll each in bread crumbs.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chili sauce over loaves.
Pour boiling water into dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Transfer loaves to a serving platter.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: mexican pronto
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Combine green chilies, taco sauce, cream of chicken soup, milk and mushroom soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese on top. Bake for approximately 15 minutes at 400°.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in order listed.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Pour in buttered casserole dish, 10 x 6 1/2-inches.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla,
and cook over medium heat until mixture is stiff and caramel color, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick. Pour into greased pan.
Cool.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut broccoli, cauliflower, onion and green pepper in small pieces.
Add sliced carrots, salt and oregano. Add sugar to white vinegar.
Mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Add salad oil to vinegar and sugar.
Pour over your vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot in the morning on low.
Leave all day.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut tortillas in bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in hot oil in a large pan (Dutch oven).
Add next 10 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add tortilla pieces, simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve with 2 to 3 tablespoons of cheese in each bowl and sprinkle with paprika.
Crisp chips go well also.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter, add all other ingredients.
Pour into shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Halve and seed squash.
Put in a shallow pan, cut side up. Stuff with sausage and sprinkle cinnamon over it.
Put water in pan halfway up the squash.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave aged steamed pudding
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Beat together butter, sugar, molasses and egg.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flour and fruit with water to creamed mixture.

title: marshmallow puffs
directions: Open can of crescent rolls and allow to warm to room temperature.
After they are easier to work with, tear off 1 roll at a time.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, set marshmallow in and roll the dough around the marshmallow.
Make sure there are no open areas.
Children love to eat and fix these.
I have to fix 3 cans at a time.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Spray a large skillet.
Stir-fry vegetables for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from pan.
In the same skillet, heat oil and stir-fry chicken until no longer pink.
Add soup, water and basil. Mix well. Add vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve over fettuccine.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all juices.
Mix and add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: beef and chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion and meat in large skillet; drain off fat.
Add grated cheese.
Heat soup, milk and Velveeta cheese until cheese is melted.
Add chilies and pimientos.
Set aside.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.
You can use different fruits.

title: hash brown supremes
directions: Mix melted butter and corn flake crumbs.
Mix together all ingredients, except 3/4 of melted butter and crumbs.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 3/4 butter/crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
May be prepared 24 hours ahead and refrigerated.

title: winx leachman's cheese and olive appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olives.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of mixture around each olive to form a small ball.
Freeze.
Bake as needed at 350° for 15 minutes and surprise those drop-in guests.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder. Add one cup at a time.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour butter over sugar and mix thoroughly. Add salt, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut and mix thoroughly. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix with mixer.
Add prunes and pecans. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes on 350°.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix first six ingredients and beat until smooth.
Dip wieners in mixture.
Fry in deep fat until brown, approximately 3 minutes. Drain on paper towel.

title: squash relish
directions: Chop vegetables fine, or grind coarse.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on medium heat for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and put in jars.
Put hot lids on and invert for 10 minutes.
Turn over and let cool.

title: mini meat loaves and veggies
directions: Mix meat, salt, egg, 1/2 tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and 1/2 onion.
Place 3 small mini loaves of this mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put vegetables around outside.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top meat with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake covered for 35 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix lightly but well.
In a separate bowl mix dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans immediately and cool on racks.
This bread may be frozen for later use.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crushed wafers and melted butter; mix well.
Press on bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, softened butter and eggs.
Beat on high speed of mixer for 15 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Spread sugar mixture on top of crust; top with bananas, then cover with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over fruit; sprinkle with nuts.
Garnish with cherry halves. Chill thoroughly; cut into squares to serve.
Yields 20 to 24 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need 1 large punch bowl.

title: fancy baked potato
directions: Peel the potato and split in half.
Salt and pepper each half. Put a large slice of onion and a pat of butter between the halves.
Wrap in bacon and seal in aluminum foil.
Bake in a 400° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sour cream and vanilla, then beat.
Add flour and soda, sifted first.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Some ovens may vary, might be 1 hour and 30 minutes.)

title: coconut topping
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch and half and half in medium size saucepan until blended.
Bring to simmering over medium heat, stirring constantly; cook 1 minute until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread over bar cookies and cakes.

title: westinghouse cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, lemon juice and eggs.
In a bowl, mix cinnamon, flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Mound in a bread pan, lined with wax paper.
Chill.
Slice off as needed.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon snowballs by janis
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, cornflake crumbs, flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well and shape into 3/4-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Place powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Add cookies (while still warm) and shake gently.
Cool on cookie sheet.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and salt together.
Take out 1 cup for top.
Mix liquid with soda and combine with dry ingredients.
Fill cups 3/4 full and top with crumbs.
Bake 350° and 25 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Place in blender bananas, sugar, egg and melted butter.
Blend 30 seconds until all ingredients are combined and bananas are mashed.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken.
Mix soup and water together. Pour in casserole dish.
Add rice.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water; add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 into bowl or pan and chill.
When chilled, spread sour cream.
Add remaining jello and chill.

title: cola cake
directions: This cake is to be mixed by hand; do not use electric mixer. Sift sugar and flour together in a large bowl.
Combine butter, shortening, cocoa and cola and heat until butter is melted; pour over flour mixture and stir well.
Add buttermilk, soda, beaten eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well and spoon into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Marshmallows will tend to gather in one section.
Distribute throughout pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Spread with Cola Topping while cake is still hot.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate nut balls
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt chocolate chips and margarine over low heat, stirring frequently.
Remove pan from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat in egg until smooth and glossy. Add sifted powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Stir in the 1/2 cup coconut and the chopped peanuts. Chill about 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional flaked coconut.
Arrange on a baking sheet. Chill at least 3 hours or until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen balls.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make into patties and place in hot greased frying pan.
Brown both sides.

title: pineapple-banana salad
directions: Cut up bananas and toss with instant pudding.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir and chill.

title: corn and bell pepper salad
directions: In a large skillet saute corn, bell pepper, garlic and cumin in oil over low to moderate heat for 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add scallions and stir for 30 seconds.
Transfer to a bowl and add lemon juice and toss.
Serve at room temperature.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in a 9 x 12 pan or a 3 quart casserole.
Melt one stick of margarine and pour over the potatoes.
Mix the chicken soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper together. This will be very thick.
Pour mixture over the potatoes and butter.
Melt the other stick of margarine and mix with the corn flakes.
Layer on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
This is definitely meant for a crowd.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put Jell-O in and mix real good.
Let cool (if in a rush, set in ice). After cool, pour in buttermilk, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour in dish.
Let congeal at least 5 to 6 hours.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: *For spicy taste, use Mexican Velveeta with regular Velveeta.

title: aunt kat's quiche
directions: Fill pie shells with vegetable, meat and cheese.
Whip eggs until foamy; fold into cream and pour into pie shells.
Put in oven at 425° and bake for 15 minutes, then turn heat down to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until puffy and browned.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute chicken breasts; arrange in oven-proof casserole dish. Add artichokes.
Mix mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over top.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in water seasoned with celery and onion.
Bone chicken and cut into bite sizes.
Place in casserole dish.
Slice boiled eggs on top.
Add soup to chicken broth; pour over chicken.

title: beanie burger
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Strain and pour in catsup and pork and beans.
Mix well and let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Spread the mixture over hamburger buns.
May be topped with cheese.
Great for a quick and easy, delicious meal.

title: light blush salad dressing
directions: In small saucepan, mix Almaden Light, vinegar and cornstarch; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Let cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: beef and rice balls
directions: Combine uncooked rice, ground beef, onion, green pepper, salt, celery salt and garlic.
Form into balls 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Heat tomato juice, cloves, cinnamon, sugar and Worcestershire sauce in a skillet on medium heat.
Drop in meat balls.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 30 minutes or until rice is fully cooked.

title: tennessee lasagna
directions: Assemble casserole in rectangular buttered dish.
Spread half of cooked macaroni.
Cover with half of Cheddar cheese and a layer of sauce.
Add another layer of cheese, macaroni and sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: new year's hopping john
directions: Cook bacon/hog jowl until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Save 3 tablespoons drippings.
Saute ham and onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in garlic powder, peas, rice, hot pepper sauce, red pepper and salt.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients for crust and press into 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lightly grease cookie sheet and roll dough into a ball.
Put some sugar in a bowl.
Get a glass and dip it in the sugar.
Mash the cookies lightly.
Take a fork and put designs on cookies. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Note:
You may substitute other fruit pie fillings.
Also great next day served with milk and sugar.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 1/4 cups or according to rice directions.
Bring to boil.
Cook rice according to box directions.
Saute onion in shortening in large skillet until tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups water, carrots and broth.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger, ketchup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Cook over low heat: sugar, flour, cocoa, syrup and milk until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Let stand a few minutes.
Then beat with mixer until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut while warm.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; crumble into small pieces.
Fry onion and ground beef until brown; drain.
In very large baking dish, combine bacon, beef, onion, catsup, sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Fold in beans and stir gently.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.
Good with corn bread or muffins.

title: chocolate shake
directions: Blend in blender until creamy.
Makes an absolutely refreshing drink.

title: meal in one for two
directions: Saute meat, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter until tender-crisp. Add salt, pepper sauce, lemon juice, rice and tomatoes. Heat thoroughly. Stir in mayonnaise. Serve topped with corn chips. Makes 2 servings.

title: peanut blossom
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients. Shape into balls. Roll balls in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and place Hershey chocolate Kiss on each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Prolonged creaming of butter and sugar is essential in making a good pound cake.
Batter should be creamed until soft and light; sugar, added gradually, beating at least 10 minutes in mixer or longer by hand.
Then eggs should be thoroughly beaten, one at a time.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over low heat. Add 1 cup sugar, flour, vanilla, eggs and nuts; mix well. Pour into buttered pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Bring the last 4 ingredients to a boil and cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and pour over cake while it is still hot.

title: indian pie
directions: Mix all together and flatten out to 1 inch in large pan.
Bake 20 or 30 minutes in 350° or 400° oven until brown.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing. Add milk and pepper. Stir while adding vinegar. Add other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned hermits
directions: Cover 2 cups raisins with cold water and boil.
Put aside to cool.
Cream together sugar, molasses and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour and baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to other mixture and mix well.
Add cooled raisins and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread in bottom of crust.
Slice 2 bananas.
Arrange on top of cream cheese mix.
Drain pineapple and spread on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle nuts of your choice.

title: gold brick candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, butter, vanilla, nuts and marshmallows. Beat until creamy.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Chill overnight.
Cut in small pieces and wrap individually. Store candy in refrigerator.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheets. Combine cake mix, whipped topping and 1 egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar:
roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
(High altitude:
No adjustment necessary.)
Children and adults alike love the tangy flavor of these cookies.

title: mother bess's pound cake
directions: Best if ingredients are at room temperature.

title: biscuit tortoni
directions: Combine liqueur and gelatin in heat-resistant cup; mix until gelatin is softened.
Place cup in simmering water; heat until gelatin is completely liquefied, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl of electric mixer until light and lemon colored.
Combine water and sugar in medium saucepan; bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved.
Reduce heat; cook until syrup registers 230° on candy thermometer, about 5 minutes.
With mixer at low speed, slowly add hot syrup to egg yolks in steady stream, beating until well blended.
Add gelatin mixture; continue beating until thick, about 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: "the best" au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix together good the hash browns, soups, onion, green pepper and grated cheese.
Mix together and put in a greased glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Sprinkle parsley and paprika on top when done.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Add oil and stir until crumbly.
Reserve and set aside 1 cup of this mixture for topping. Add 1 cup buttermilk or 1 cup milk with 1 teaspoon vinegar to remaining mixture.
Beat in egg and baking soda.
Turn batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, pour in beans and level them.
Bake (optional) in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top beans with sauce, then the tomatoes, lettuce, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Use chips to dip.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix; roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 5 tablespoons sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 275°.
Yield: 100.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put in freezer to harden.
Roll into small balls; put on wax paper and place back into
the freezer.
Dip in chocolate with toothpick.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut pieces of bacon in half and layer over top.
Spread a little mustard over bacon.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir ingredients together in the order given.
Refrigerate dough for at least 12 hours.
(Dough may be kept in the refrigerator several days.)
Roll dough into your favorite shape on a slightly floured board; let rise 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen rolls.

title: kay's beans
directions: Layer green beans, water chestnuts and corn in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream, onion and Cheddar cheese. Pour over vegetables.
Mix margarine, crackers and garlic powder. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: snack attack
directions: Measure into bowl.
Mix together with crackers.
Crackers will be greasy.
Put crackers into a bag (brown) and add dry Ranch dressing.
Hold bag shut and shake about 30 times.

title: johnny marzetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion & pepper.
Add chili powder, tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Add cooked noodles.
Top with cheese and bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Season to taste.
Mix well. Put in salad bowl.
Put strips of red and green pepper on top.
Chill.

title: grace's brownies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in prepared 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tested done.
Cool.
Cut in 2-inch squares to serve.

title: blueberry yogurt muffins
directions: Mix together all-purpose flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Make well in center and add vanilla, orange juice, vegetable oil, low-fat yogurt and egg.
Lastly, add blueberries. Stir until moistened.
Divide batter into 12 muffin cups (line with paper cups, optional).
Sprinkle a bit of sugar over muffins. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: no-fat layered taco dip
directions: Place refried beans on platter. Spread sour cream on top of beans.
Add hamburger, lettuce and onion.
Spread salsa on top of all ingredients.
Top with cheese. All ingredients will be layered when finished. Dip with guiltless gourmet taco chips or any nonfat chips.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: Spread 1 cup croutons in lightly greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Combine soups, salad dressing and packet of dry soup; spread over croutons.
Top with chicken, broccoli, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Spread with remaining cup of croutons.
Cover loosely with foil and bake in 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix with mixer on medium until well mixed.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; set aside.
Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar; blend in egg.
Then add to sifted dry ingredients. Mix in applesauce, chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Let set a few minutes so flavors can blend.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In bowl, combine cheese, egg, crumbs, garlic and softened butter.
Remove stems from mushrooms; place unfilled mushrooms rounded side up on baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter; broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove and turn; fill with mixture.
Return filled mushrooms to broiler; broil 1 to 2 minutes more.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Top with Cool Whip mixed with your favorite fruit or pie filling.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Measure flour and add baking powder.
Put aside.
Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Add lemon flavoring.
Add half the flour mixture with 1/2 cup buttermilk. Mix well.

title: jerry d's crab cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with crab meat.
Mix egg, mustard, mayonnaise and Worcestershire and blend it gently together by hand with the crab meat mix.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 5 crab cakes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch glass dish until set.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients. Roll in waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: three bean salad(weight watchers)
directions: Drain beans.
Combine with onions in mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, combine vinegar, oil, sweetener, salt and pepper. Mix well. Pour over beans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat together butter, sugar and egg, then stir in peanut butter and chocolate; gradually stir in flour alternately with milk.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares. Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken tenders with tarragon and mustard sauce
directions: Heat vermouth, chicken stock, garlic and 1 teaspoon tarragon in a large skillet. When liquid starts to boil, add chicken, lower heat and poach chicken about 5 to 7 minutes. Turn as needed; do not overcook.
Remove chicken to plate and keep warm.
Moisten starch with skim milk and add to liquid in skillet with remaining teaspoon tarragon.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Add mustard and mix.
Add chicken.
Heat about 1 minute.
If sauce seems too thick, add a little chicken broth.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla and flour.
Add nuts. Shape into small crescents.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until very lightly browned.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat thoroughly.
Cook in deep fat as you do cornbread or hush puppies.

title: peas and rice
directions: Fry together the onion, tomatoes and seasoning in pork fat for 15 minutes. Add 1 1/2 pints water and peas. Simmer 15 more minutes. Add 1 quart rice and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes on low flame.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Place on bottom of dish.
Pour sauce over beef.
Add pepperoni, peppers, onion, mushrooms or your other favorite topping.
Add cheese.
Roll out crescent rolls and cover top with dough.
Cook until dough browns.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook to form a soft ball. Remove form heat. Add walnut meats. Stir to coat each piece.
Lay out separately on waxed paper. When dry it will have a white glaze.

title: wilted cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Add 1 cup sugar; let stand.
In a saucepan, mix 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, celery seed, vinegar and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: woodford's pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Bake in lightly greased loaf pan in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until fairly firm in center.
Let cool some to set.
Good served with Cool Whip or other topping.
(Can also be put in shallower pan and cooked in slower oven, but we like it crusty.)

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Blend in cocoa and red food coloring.
Sift together cake flour, salt and soda.
Mix buttermilk and vinegar.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Bake in layers, tube or Bundt pans that have been heavily greased (not floured) with a solid shortening (not butter, margarine or oil) at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Allow to rest for 20 minutes without inverting before removing from pan.
Makes 12 servings.
Preparation time: 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour meat on both sides with first four ingredients combined. Brown on both sides.
Also brown the onions, then add tomatoes and simmer for 2 hours.

title: fusilli with tomato and olive sauce
directions: In a large skillet heat oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is soft, but not brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes, olives, capers, vinegar, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes on low heat.
While sauce is cooking, put pasta on to boil.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add pasta to sauce and toss.
Mix in cheese and serve immediately with some additional grated Romano cheese on the side.

title: lite ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit such as: strawberries, bananas, tart apple slices, pineapple spears, etc. Makes 2 cups.
Can also be used as a topping for fruit salad. Four tablespoons equal 100 calories.
With traditional ingredients equals 215 calories.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or two 8-inch pans. Set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add all together and keep in refrigerator.

title: bailey's chilli
directions: Soak and cook pinto beans until almost done.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add to beans.
Saute onions, garlic and green pepper until tender.
Add to beans and meat.
Add tomato sauce, paste and spices and simmer for at least an hour.
Stir frequently and add additional water and spices to desired taste and consistency.
Serve plain or over rice.
Grated Cheddar cheese and chopped green onion make good toppings.
Serves approximately 15.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Beat in already beaten eggs.
Mix in chocolate chips and set aside.

title: spaghetti and chicken
directions: Boil and debone one chicken (save broth).
Layer chicken pieces in a casserole dish.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in melted margarine until tender.
Pour over chicken pieces; salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup chicken broth.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, eggs, milk and spices. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and line with waxed paper. Pour mixture into wax paper-lined pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle nuts over cake mix and spoon melted margarine over nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Remove from oven; let cool. Invert; remove waxed paper. Cool and frost; cut in squares.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon over medium heat.
Add minced onion and fry slowly until transparent.
Add flour.
Boil together vinegar, water and sugar.
Add this boiled mixture to bacon, onion and flour mixture. Slice potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add chopped celery.
Pour mixture over potatoes and keep warm until ready to serve.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk in top of double boiler; remove from heat and add pecan halves.
Drop by spoonfuls (about 3 pecan halves) onto buttered cookie sheet and set in refrigerator for 3 to 5 hours or set in deep freeze for about 45 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: In 2-quart baking dish, place chicken, cut in large pieces. Spread soup over chicken.
Top with mushrooms and sliced Swiss cheese.
Top with stuffing that has been crushed into crumbs.
Dot with 1/2 cup butter.
Cover; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Whip cream cheese, sour cream, cumin, taco sauce and garlic salt until smooth.
Spread in flat container.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Put on top of spread. Serve with Doritos.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put all ingredients together in a large cooker; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 3 1/2 hours. Makes about 6 pints.

title: denver pudding
directions: Mix together and sift 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder, sifted flour and salt.
Add 3 tablespoons cocoa, melted butter, milk and vanilla.
Spread into a greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Then sprinkle
1/2 cup white sugar on top. Then sprinkle 1/4 cup cocoa on top.
Last, pour the cold water on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugars together. Add egg and beat well until fluffy. Add flour gradually. Turn onto a board to work in the last of the flour.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in skillet, add sugar, let brown slightly.
Add juice, salt and pepper.
Cook drained carrots in this mixture until they are glazed.
Serves 6.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Cut half of white bread and half of wheat bread with biscuit cutter.
Cut other half with doughnut cutter.
Make sure both cutters are the same size.
Spread bread that was cut with biscuit cutter with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Put filling on top of this.
Put white bread with hole in middle on top of wheat bread that has filling on top.
Put hole from wheat bread in middle.
Do the opposite with white bread.
Do this until all the bread is used.
This is really better with peanut butter and grape jelly, but my mama frowns on that for parties.

title: dad's potato croquettes
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, eggs and Parmesan in a large bowl. Mix well with a fork (do not use an electric mixer).
Add bread crumbs.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and onion powder. Shape mixture into logs about 3-inches long and 2-inches wide.
Pour 1/4-inch oil into a large skillet; add a few croquettes.
Saute until browned on the bottom. Turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper toweling; keep warm on a paper towel lined, ovenproof dish in warm, 200° oven while sauteing remaining croquettes. Makes 5 generous servings.

title: scalloped chicken supreme
directions: Make creamy
gravy
with
butter, broth, milk, salt and pepper. Also cook
the rice in 2 cups water until done.
Layer in 12
x
8 x 2-inch dish the rice, chicken and gravy (sprinkling over each
layer
the
mushooms,
pimentos and almonds). Top with crumbs mixed with 1 tablespoon butter.
May refrigerate for a few hours, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: grandma broesamle's fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball, 236°, the sugar, milk, cocoa and corn syrup. Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool!
Stir until candy starts to lose gloss.
Add nuts and pour into pan.

title: pearl's banana bread(originally from pearl dunbar, who is baking this in heaven!)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening with bananas.
Add eggs, flour and soda and stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts and stir well.
Pour into a loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salade nicoise
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 2 inches of water to boiling.
Add potatoes and green beans.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or just until tender.
Remove beans with a slotted spoon; drain potatoes. Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.

title: crunchy onion twists
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Twist one dough strip and shape into a ring; pinch ends together.
Twist remaining breadsticks.
Place ring and breadsticks on baking sheet.
Brush top side of all breadsticks with egg white.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients. Bake for 15 minutes until golden brown.
To serve, insert sticks through ring.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch, and 1/4 cup sugar. Rub in butter with fingers until mixture is crumbly and no large particles remain.
Place in an ungreased 8 or 9-inch round baking dish with a removable bottom.
Firmly press out dough into an even layer.
With tines of a fork, make impressions around edge of dough, then prick surface evenly.
Bake in 325° oven about 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut while still hot into 8 to 12 wedges.
Sprinkle with sugar and cool.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Add all ingredients together, except potatoes.
Heat to boil. Add potatoes and mix carefully.
Enjoy hot or cold.

title: old fashioned peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 teaspoon or more to roll and press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Very good.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Heat through and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: rachel's pink punch
directions: Boil sugar in water with lemon, cut and squeezed and thrown in.
Add cinnamon.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and lemon rind.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze cherries, strawberries, mandarin oranges, etc. in circle mold to float in center of punch bowl.
Seven-Up or ginger ale is optional.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese; add pineapple.
Mix well with a fork. Add bell pepper.
Add onion.
Add onion salt; mix well with a fork.
Put in small serving bowl; sprinkle pecans over the top. Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Eat with crackers.
Makes an excellent Christmas appetizer.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon until tender.
Combine egg and sour cream.
Stir in cooked onion, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper, nutmeg and ginger.
Add meat.
Mix well by hand.
Shape into 3/4 inch balls.
In large skillet brown balls in remaining butter.
Remove from skillet.
Stir in flour, bouillon graduals, and coffee crystals into pan juices.
Add water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add meat balls and occasionally baste while simmering for 30 minutes in covered pan.

title: old-fashion baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Cook slowly to the boiling point. Drain.
Cover them again with water and simmer long and slowly. After 2 or 3 hours, place a few beans in a spoon; blow on them. If the skin bursts, they are sufficiently cooked.
Drain.

title: anise creole
directions: Trim base of anise bulb and discard with stalks.
Cut bulb into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent.
Bake in microwave for 2 minutes on High. Serves 3 or 4.

title: apple crisp(healthful eating)
directions: Place apples in a deep dish; sprinkle with lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together in mixer until smooth. Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, and add slowly.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing in 1/2 cup milk as needed.
After mixture is all mixed, add another 1/2 cup milk with 1 teaspoon baking powder dissolved into milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in large pan, 9 x 12-inch character pans.
(Recipe may be cut in half if a large cake is not desired.)
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending how deep pan is.
A 9 x 12-inch takes only 1 hour.
Check at 50 minutes.

title: shepardess' pie
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in skillet; add vegetables and stir to blend.
Place in greased casserole.
Spread mashed potatoes over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Prepare package of dressing as directed but also adding egg and water.
Place dressing mixture over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguini for 8 minutes in boiling water.
Chop all vegetables and mix together.
Pour 1/2 bottle of Season-All and Italian dressing over vegetables and mix well.
Stir in linguini. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Add enough water to frozen lemonade to make 1 pint of liquid. Mix cornstarch and granulated sugar together and add to lemonade mixture. Cook until transparent looking (not too thick). Serve on lemon cake or anytime a lemon sauce is needed.

title: date balls
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
When cool enough to handle, shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Melt cheese over low heat; add soups, onions and milk.
Steam broccoli; add to cheese mixture and heat.

title: fettuccini cream sauce
directions: Combine cream and melted butter to room temperature.
Add beaten egg to first mixture, whisk.
Combine with precooked noodles, cheese and seasonings.
Add fresh parsley, if desired. Mix to warm over low heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: acorn squash with applesauce
directions: Cut squash in half; place in baking dish, center down.
Cook for 1/2 hour in a 325° oven.
Remove from oven.
Turn squash upright; fill center with applesauce.
Bake for 30 minutes longer. Serve.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry several pieces of bacon, cut in small pieces.
Before bacon is done, add onion.
When bacon and onions have cooled slightly, add to drained potatoes.
Add corn, clams and milk.* Let simmer to become warm through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and salt in boiling water until done (approximately 20 minutes).
Drain well.
Mix in beaten eggs, milk and most of sharp cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole (2-quart size).
Top with rest of cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: lignia salad
directions: Cook noodles in water and little oil.
Drain, but don't wash. While noodles are hot, mix all other ingredients in; stir a few times.
Let stand at least 12 hours or overnight.
You can serve hot or cold.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to pkg. directions; drain well and set aside. Combine cream cheese and butter; beat at medium speed with a mixer until smooth. Stir in spinach. Spoon into a lightly greased 1 qt. casserole dish; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Microwave directions: Cover and microwave on high for 5 to 6 minutes, giving dish a half-turn after 3 minutes.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown meats and drain off fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add sugars, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses and seasonings.
Mix well. Add beans. Stir and pour mixture into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Important:
Mix cornstarch into sugar before cooking.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a large bowl and let set overnight.

title: potato buns
directions: Stiffen with 6 cups enriched flour.
After first few cups flour, mix well.
The last flour, knead in.
Let raise until double in bulk.
Then put buns in pan.
Let raise to double in size.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: ruby's hot dog chili from 10 cents store
directions: Chop onions in a little butter.
Put meat in and mix.
Add soup and chili powder.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: sausage scallopini
directions: Boil sausage until done.
Slice sausage into quarter-size, then fry.
Mix peppers and onions in skillet and saute until done.
When all is cooked, put into lasagna pan in layers, example:
sauce on bottom, then peppers, onions, layer of sausage, layer of cheese and repeat steps.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cajun pork chops
directions: Combine paprika, cumin, salt, sage, pepper, garlic powder, and cayenne in a bowl. Coat chops with seasoning mixture on both sides. Heat butter and oil over high heat in a large skillet until very hot. Place chops in skillet, reduce heat to medium and cook 7 to 8 minutes, turning once halfway through cooking time.

title: heavenly fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter; stir to mix.
Pour this over corn flakes until well coated.
Pour out on wax paper.
Let cool, then break into small pieces.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, cocoa and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Slowly add milk and heat on moderate temperature, stirring until thick. Remove from heat and add one teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue made from egg whites.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Chop broccoli and onion fine.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs, then add raisins and water.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix; drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.

title: turkey sausage
directions: In large mixing bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate a few hours.
Divide mixture into patties. Freeze unused portion for a later date.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add 1 cup crushed cornflakes to butter and sprinkle on top of potato casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
This can be made the day before and reheated. Good!

title: easy breakfast
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Cook until still moist and let cool and add sour cream. Put in shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and crumble cooked bacon. Chill overnight. Cook at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground cranberries and sugar together; let stand for 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: stuffed peppers(serving size: 16)
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in skillet until meat is browned.
Add rest of seasonings and tomato soup; simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts.
Stir in rice; cool.
Cut peppers in half, lengthwise, remove membrane and seeds.
Cook in boiling salt water, until barely tender, about 2 1/2 minutes; drain and cool.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix and store as salt.

title: best peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and salt together in saucepan; gradually add milk and cook over low heat until thickened.
Add egg yolks to 1/2 hot mixture.
Return to pan.
Cook, stirring constantly; take off heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool. Sprinkle 1/2 peanut butter over crust, then custard and then rest of peanut butter mixture.
Pour on meringue and brown.

title: holiday mini cheese cakes
directions: Place small vanilla wafers in paper cup liners set on a tray of your choice.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip, vanilla extract and almond extract until well blended.
Place in paper cup liners on top of wafer.
Spoon on cherry pie filling or filling of your choice.
Chill and serve.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage; place in boiling water.
Remove leaves as they wilt.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Take wilted cabbage leaf and place one tablespoon of meat mixture in leaf.
Fold one side of leaf over mixture and roll.
Tuck in other end of leaf gently but firmly.
When rolls are ready, place one can of sauerkraut in bottom of a large pot, then the rolls and finally add the other can of sauerkraut.
Add tomato sauce and enough water to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until done.
Makes 15 to 20 cabbage rolls.

title: biscuit chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken, milk, mushrooms, soup and onion.
Heat in microwave until hot.
Pour in baking dish.
Make biscuits.
Dip in Parmesan cheese and place on top.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with Twinkies.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour over Twinkies. Next, layer sliced bananas, then strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat.
Set aside to cool.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
