Dice green pepper and tomatoes. Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients except taco chips.
Just before serving, crush chips slightly and toss with salad.

title: citrus marinade(for pork, chicken or fish)
directions: In a large, nonreactive bowl, combine all ingredients. Marinate pork, chicken or fish.
Pork and chicken may be marinated all day.
Grill meat or fish.
Remaining marinade may be heated at medium-high until reduced and pour over.

title: roasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Melt candy coating in a double boiler.
Cool 2 minutes and then add pecans.
Stir until all is coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool completely.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Prepare carrots and place in bottom of steamer pan over boiling water.
Prepare cauliflower and place in pan on top of carrots.
Prepare broccoli and place in pan on top of cauliflower. Steam until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Remove from heat and drain.
Pour into a colander and rinse with cold water.
Place in a bowl and pour over a mixture of dressing, salt, pepper and sweetener.
Stir gently to mix.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally to mix.

title: washday soup
directions: Cover beans, peas, rice and barley with cold water and let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil in the same water, adding vegetables, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Add ham bone and simmer about 1 hour longer.
If water cooks away, add a bit more from time to time.
Remove ham bone, pick off bits of meat and return them to soup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party time beans
directions: In slow cooker.........combine the first 10 ingredients, mix well. Add the beans and peas,
cover and cook on low for 5-7 hours or	until onion and peppers are tender. Remove bay leaves.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute beef and onions in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add tomato paste, spices, salt and pepper.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Put in large shallow greased baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Boil noodles and salt.
Boil for 12 minutes.
Add remaining olive oil and cool.
Put a layer of noodles on greased pan.
Add hamburger sauce, then half of the cheeses.
Make 2 layers.
On top layer, put a layer of noodles before last layer of Mozzarella cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes in salted boiling water.
When tender, drain.
Layer casserole dish with potatoes and cheese. Mix together soup and water.
Pour mix over potatoes and cheese. Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix
well
first 6 ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at
for 35 minutes or until pie is set when shaken. Recipe may
be
doubled
to make 3 pies.
May be frozen after baking.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Put warm water in large bowl; add yeast with mixer at low speed.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Increase mixer speed and slowly add 2 cups flour.
Stir in 2 more cups of flour with a spoon.
(If needed, add a little more flour at a time until dough is workable.)
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Knead dough down in bowl 5 or 6 times.
Make up into rolls.
Let rise 20 minutes and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This dough makes good cinnamon rolls.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion and butter in a large Dutch oven until onion is translucent.
Add soup and milk.
Heat through.
Add broccoli, salt and pepper to taste.
You can sprinkle grated cheese over the top before serving.
Quick, easy and delicious!!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, carrots and pineapple. Mix in dry ingredients and blend well.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured cake pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix other ingredients except fruit.
Pour over crust.
Top with fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix the flour, margarine
and pecans.
Press into a large oblong pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: brazil-nut stuffing
directions: Turn stuffing into bowl.
Add cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Toss to distribute seasonings.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add Brazil nuts and cook until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Combine water and raisins in a pot.
Bring to boil.
Pour over stuffing. Stir in diced apple.
Will stuff one chicken (about 4 pounds).

title: island punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice (except 2 cups), tropical punch, coconut flavoring.
In medium saucepan, combine the reserved 2 cups pineapple juice with the sugar.
Heat until sugar dissolves. Add to punch mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, add 7-Up or Sprite.

title: italian eggplant with beef(yields 6 servings)
directions: Brown the ground beef (can substitute ground turkey).
Just before meat is done, add chopped onion and clove of crushed garlic.
Cook until onion is done.
Add sliced eggplant and crushed tomatoes (can use stewed tomatoes) to beef mixture.
Add seasonings.
Cook until eggplant is tender.
Add bread crumbs and fresh grated Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Take sweet milk and let boil for 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and a little pinch of salt and soda.
Stir in cornmeal (enough to make a moderately thin batter).
Cover and set in a warm place overnight.
Early the next morning, take a quart of warm water, put a level teaspoon of salt in it and stir in flour (enough to make a rather stiff batter).
Then stir in the cornmeal yeast. Sit in a pot of warm water and cover it.
Stir once if too long coming.
To keep the water at an even temperature, not too hot to bear the hand in.
Let the yeast stand until it rises in a fine foam.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in water.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat. Add eggs, rice and other ingredients.
Cook over low heat until heated through, then serve.

title: anna's zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in pizza pan that has been buttered and floured.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Clean leeks thoroughly.
Cut off ends.
Cut off and discard long green stems.
Split lengthwise from stem end, turn and split one more time.
Separate under running water, making sure all dirt has been washed away, then chop into 1/4 inch pieces.
Peel potatoes and cut them into 1/4-inch cubes (about 2 cups).
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan, add onions and leeks and cook over medium heat, stirring until wilted, not brown.
Add chicken broth, water, bay leaf, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Remove from heat.
Remove bay leaf.
Add remaining butter.
Stir.
Adjust seasoning.
Serve.

title: calico cabbage
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole and add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: senate cheese straws
directions: Finely grate cheese.
Combine with other ingredients and beat until creamy, adding a few drops of water if necessary to form a firm dough.
Divide the dough in half; roll each section 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into strips about 6 x 3/8-inch.
Twist and place on a ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill in freezer 15 minutes or longer to maintain shape.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Place baking cups in muffin pan.
Place one vanilla wafer in each cup. Fill approximately 2/3 full with cream cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Top with pie filling; refrigerate.

title: crabmeat cheese appetizers(shared by mary jane dudley)
directions: Combine butter and cheese and mix.
Add crabmeat, salt and mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Spread on muffin.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: In a heavy pan, stir in sugar, salt and buttermilk.
Cook to 234° or soft ball stage, stirring as necessary to keep from sticking (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
(Do not stir.)
Cool 30 minutes.
Quickly stir in pecans and beat for 3 minutes until slightly thickened and drop on wax paper.

title: gingerbread students
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cool dough.
Cut with cutters.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: caramel divinity roll
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a medium-size heavy saucepan.
Heat quickly to boiling, stirring constantly.
Wrap a fork with damp paper toweling and wipe the sugar crystals from side of pan as the mixture cooks.
Reduce heat to medium and cook without stirring to 260° on a candy thermometer.
(A spoonful of syrup will form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.)

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Lay turkey out flat as possible on a cutting board, placing skin side down.
Combine garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in food processor or bender.
Begin processing and add oil gradually. Chop until just coarse.

title: po man's beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add meat until brown.
Then stir in tomato sauce and sour cream.
Cook on low heat until cooked together well.

title: mexican super dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning and cream cheese.
Spread on 14-inch pan or plate.
Cover with salsa.
Add onions, tomatoes, peppers and olives.
Cover entirely with cheeses.
Serve with plain nachos.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
The pie filling coats all fruit.

title: new england lobster newburg
directions: Cook seafood.
Pour sherry over seafood and let sit.
Melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour (low heat), slowly.
Add salt, mustard, cayenne and mushrooms.
Add cream slowly.
Cook until thick.
Add to seafood and sherry. Cover with butter and crumbs. Cook at 375° in casserole pan 10 minutes. Serve over egg noodles or cook in puff pastry.

title: easy and quick onion rice
directions: Soften butter in a
pot; add 1 can Campbell's onion soup and a can beef stock; wash rice and mix together until it boils.
Cover pot; lower flame and cook for 20 minutes, mixing at least twice.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and orange juice according to package directions. Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl and chill. Before serving, add chilled ginger ale.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs in small mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and cook as package directs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix milk, sugar and half of the coconut.
Bring to a boil and pour over hot cake.
Let cool and spread Cool Whip on top of cake. Sprinkle remaining coconut on top.

title: "old time" egg custard pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs with other ingredients except nutmeg.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn down oven to 325° and cook 30 to 35 minutes.
Add meringue, if desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease and line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread crumbs.
Place layer of toast.
Brown and drain sausage; put thin layer of sausage and cheese on toast.
Repeat process until all is used, two layers each.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper and milk.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Warm all ingredients to room temperature; blend well.
May want to add garlic salt or powder, onion salt or powder or other seasonings.

title: marinated hamsteak
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Combine pineapple juices, garlic powder, chili powder and oregano.
Pour over pork.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or longer.
Remove pork from marinade (marinade can be added to the cooking liquid for noodles or rice).
Broil 2 to 4-inches from heat source, for almost 5 minutes each side.
Serves 4.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Top with onion rings.
Warm in microwave or heat in oven until warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Roll in pecans until covered.
Store in refrigerator.

title: no knead icebox rolls
directions: To first 5 ingredients, add 6 cups of flour.
Stir well.
Cover and let rise in warm place an hour or more.
Work out on floured board.
Pour oil in 3 (9-inch) pans.
Place rolls in pan and cover with Saran Wrap and put in icebox until 1 hour before cooking.
Set in warm place, leaving Saran Wrap in place to prevent drying out. When ready to bake, remove Saran Wrap and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter, garlic and oil in skillet.
Add shrimp and saute until done, about 3 minutes.
Pour off drippings into small saucepan.
Add other ingredients.
Cook over high heat about 1 minute.
Pour sauce over shrimp.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Keep in tightly sealed jar.
For 1 serving, use 1 teaspoon in 3/4 cup hot water.
To make 1 quart, use 3/4 cup mix to hot water.

title: grandmaw jordan's pumpkin pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°. Makes 3 pies.

title: pleasant hill best beets
directions: Saute onion lightly in butter until soft, but not brown. Drain beets and place them in onion and butter.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Toss beets, adding salt.
Heat until hot.
(Tiny whole beets are best.)

title: apple dumplings
directions: Using a deep ovenproof pan, put water 1 1/2 inches deep.
Add sugar and butter.
Boil until thin syrup.
Roll dough thin; cut into 5-inch squares.
Put 3 tablespoons applesauce in center of each square and top with pat of butter.
Bring corners together and seal seams tightly.
Place into boiling syrup, filling pan. Put pat of butter on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip together; first add can of cherry pie filling.
Stir.
Add drained pineapple; stir, then add chopped pecans.
Stir.
Chill.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir apples into batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Chill 30 minutes to 4 hours. Yields 4 servings.
Has 225 calories, fat free.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Put potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pour margarine over potatoes.
Mix rest of ingredients together. Spread over potatoes. Top with corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter together and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on a greased pan.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in a heavy casserole dish.
Cook onion in butter over moderate high heat until transparent.
Add the rice, stirring to coat the grains with butter.
Pour in the stock or water. Add salt and pepper. Bring to boil over high heat.
Add the seasonings to the rice.
Cover.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins about 1 hour, cool and peel.
Melt butter in microwave, blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and cook until thickened (approximately 8 minutes).
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Dice potatoes and place in baking dish; cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until browned and heated thoroughly.

title: easy noodles
directions: Prepare pasta as noted on package.
Cook and drain.
Mix milk and onion sauce and pour and mix through pasta and serve immediately.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and cabbage until soft.
Add potatoes and brown.
Sprinkle flour over all until margarine or butter is absorbed, stirring constantly.
Pour in milk.
While mixture comes to a boil, add basil, garlic salt and pepper.
After mixture has boiled, simmer on low until ready to serve.
Sprinkle grated cheese and green onion over top as desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain cans of Veg-All and put in casserole dish.
Add water chestnuts.
Melt Cheez Whiz and margarine.
Mix and pour over vegetables.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large pan, cook onions until tender, but not brown.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook on low heat until near boiling.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
Improves with standing.
Better the next day.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, salt, vanilla and milk.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites to very soft peaks.
Gently fold into milk mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onions, bread crumbs and mushroom soup.
Beat egg and fold into mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart flat casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs over top; dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 4-layer lemon delight
directions: Mix well.
Press on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: turkey chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Crumble turkey into skillet.
Cook until brown. Stir in chili powder, oregano and salt.
Cook a few seconds.
Stir in tomatoes.
Bring mixture to boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.
Stir in beans; cook thoroughly.

title: chocolate marshmallow roll
directions: Put marshmallows and walnuts in large bowl.
Melt margarine or butter with Baker's chocolate on low heat.
Add to egg, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over marshmallows and walnuts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry pudding.
Add drained pineapple, walnuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Mix in mixer until it is all mixed together about 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
When you get it out of oven, spread butter on top until melted.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and sugar.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Heat milk; add sugar and butter.
Place in large warm bowl. Add 2 eggs and 3 cups flour.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to mixture.
Add 2 to 3 more cups flour and knead for 10 minutes. Place in large, greased bowl, greasing top of dough, too.
Cover with dry towel and let rise until double in size.
Punch down, divide in two.
Place in 2 greased pie tins and allow to rise again, covered.
Brush additional beaten egg on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer until ready to serve.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix sour cream and Jell-O.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir.
Nuts may be added.

title: bacon-spinach pie(for dutch oven)
directions: Prepare pie crust, bake for 5 minutes and set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Mix bacon, cheese, spinach and cracker crumbs.
Beat eggs; combine with milk and add to mixed ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake pie 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish and top with cheese.
Thin soup with water.
Mix until smooth and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ricotta stuffed eggplant
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a medium skillet, saute green pepper, mushrooms, thyme, salt and pepper in 1 tablespoon oil, stirring frequently until all liquid is evaporated.
Cool.
Cut eggplant lengthwise in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange on broiler rack. Brush eggplant with mix of remaining oil and garlic.
Broil 2 minutes per side, basting with oil mix.

title: ultra low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl combine applesauce, sugars, vanilla and Egg Beaters until well blended.
Add flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes, until edges are golden brown. Makes 5 dozen cookies; 67 calories per serving, 1.7 fat per serving.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: In butter, lightly brown chicken breasts.
Arrange in baking dish.

Combine chicken soup, mushrooms, water chestnuts, green peppers, a pinch of salt, pepper and cooking wine (optional). Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and uncovered for 1/2 hour. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 8.

title: flemish beef and beer
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil, then remove and saute meat which has been seasoned with salt and pepper and dusted with flour.
Brown meat and remove excess oil.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, place meat, then onions.
Top with the rest of ingredients in their order and cover tightly, baking in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Delicious served with spatzle or noodles.

title: meal in one dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain and add 2 cups mushroom soup, 1 cup sweet peas, 1 cup corn and 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Then add onions and mushrooms that you've sauteed in butter.
Put in pie shells.
Fix instant potatoes as directed on box.
Put on top of each filling in pie.
Then put your cheese on top of each pie. (It can be your favorite cheese.)
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or until pie shells are done, depending on your oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until done and debone. Drain cooked spaghetti. Cook onion and green pepper until tender. Add soup, chicken broth, cheese, Ro-Tel, chicken, salt and pepper. Put spaghetti in casserole dish; pour chicken mixture over spaghetti. Top with more cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternating with sour cream.
Add flavoring.

title: party punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to package.
Add pineapple juice and freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before party.
Serve slushy.
This makes 1 gallon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; place in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and eggs.
Pour over broccoli.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place onions on top.
Bake another 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: apricot bars
directions: Can use other fruit.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix juices and water.
Add ginger ale.
Add sherbet just before serving.

title: pheasant bistro style
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in grocery bag.
Shake with pheasant until lightly coated.
Place skin side down on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes, turn once. Discard melted fat.
Place cooked pheasant in ovenproof casserole. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover.
Cook until sauce thickens.

title: mini pizza appetizer
directions: Spread sauce on English muffin.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toast in oven at 375° about 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix evaporated milk, mushroom soup, chicken soup, chicken broth and butter.
Heat 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Add dressing to mix; turn and pour over chicken.
Cook 12 minutes on High, uncovered.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and put in pan.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and cook potatoes until tender.
Sprinkle with flour and mix.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine orange	juice concentrate, lemon juice, pineapple juice and cherry juice;
mix well.	Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add cold ginger ale.
Garnish
with berries and pineapple spears, if desired.
Yields 25 punch cup servings.

title: swiss chicken bake
directions: Place chicken on the bottom of a greased 9x13 inch pan.
Lay the cheese on the top.
Mix the soup with the wine or water and pour over top of chicken.
Sprinkle the crushed bread cubes over soup.
Finally, drizzle the melted butter over bread cubes.
Bake for one hour at 350° or until top is browned.
Serve over rice.

title: ten layer salad
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer ingredients in order: lettuce, onion, bell pepper, cauliflower, peas, mayonnaise, sugar, dressing mix, bacon bits and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Will keep about 4 days.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Cool.
Cream together remaining ingredients and spread over baked crust.
Top with finely chopped vegetables of your choice.
Cover pizza with shredded cheese.

title: pecan catfish
directions: In a small bowl, combine the milk, Dijon mustard and cayenne pepper.
Dip fillets into mustard mixture.
Then dip into ground pecans, shaking off excess.
Place on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes and pecans are browned.

title: mexi dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Dip
can
be frozen and reheated.	Serve with taco chips.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind up Oreos until they look like potting soil in food processor. Set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cut onions into fourths.
Add 1 can milk to mushroom soup; pour over onions.
Add enough grated American cheese to add color of yellow and taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: no-oil pesto
directions: Place broth in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place basil, spinach, cheese, garlic and oregano in a food processor or blender. Add hot broth and blend well, adding more broth to make a smooth paste-like sauce.
Cook and drain pasta; immediately toss pesto sauce with pasta.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix flour, salt and soda and add to batter.
Last add crushed potato chips and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Press down on ungreased cookie sheet with floured fork.
Bake at 325°
for 10 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pick off bone.
Cut into pieces and line pan. Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Put stuffing on top of this.
Melt margarine and spoon on top.
Spoon chicken broth over this.
Put in oven and bake until it starts to bubble, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Heat molasses to almost boiling.
Pour over margarine mixture.
Add vinegar, cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 beaten egg.
Sift together and add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: lillie's frillies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form into small balls. Roll in white or colored coconut.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts, raisins or dates.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, sour cream and milk (set aside). Take potato rounds and line a flat glass casserole enough to line bottom of the casserole with one layer. Alternate soup mix, bits of butter (margarine), bacon bits, cheese and onion bits and build each layer to the top, sprinkling salt, pepper and garlic powder on each layer. Sprinkle some of the cheese on top and sprinkle a little pepper on that the last 15 minutes of baking time. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until potatoes feel soft.

title: quick and easy chicken alfredo
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces and saute in vegetable oil. Combine heavy cream, Italian salad dressing mix and Parmesan cheese in a saucepan; cook on low to medium heat until ingredients are smooth.
Add the sauteed chicken and serve with your favorite pasta.
Recipe will serve 2 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on the box.
Using an oblong pan, put the ingredients in this order: margarine, sugar, fruit cocktail and last the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake(it's as delicious as it is quick)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine Quick Mix and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add half of milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes, until batter is smooth.
Add remaining milk mixture and beat 3 more minutes.
Pour into prepared pan and spread evenly.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately spread with Lazy Daisy Topping.
Return cake to oven and broil 3 to 4 minutes, until topping becomes bubbly and light brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 large cake.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Separate yolks from whites and boil with remaining ingredients for 1 minute.
Immediately stir in gelatin.
Cool.
When partially set, whip.
Whip egg whites with: 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt, then add peanut butter, butter and egg to it.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into balls.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake until light brown, 9 to 10 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash and remove seeds from chilies and let soak in cold water for 1 hour; drain.
Lay chilies flat in bottom of baking dish. Put grated cheeses on top.
Mix egg, flour, milk and salt.
Lay more chilies on top of cheese.
Pour milk mixture over top of cheese, then more chilies on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: country style macaroni
directions: Boil 5 cups water; add potatoes, cabbage and macaroni with salt.
Stir often.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter with olive oil.
Add onion and ham cubes.
Stir in pinch of salt and pepper.
Add wine, parsley and marjoram.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put together this sauce and macaroni mixture.
Add remaining melted 3 tablespoons butter and cheese on top.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in crock-pot; cover with sliced onion.
Combine garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in water.
Pour over meat.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar,
oil,
water and pie filling. Add flour, baking soda, salt
and
cinnamon and mix well.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Set oven at 350°.
Put in three 9-inch loaf pans, 1/3 batter in each pan.
Bake 1 hour or until bread pulls away from sides of pans.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Cool loaves on rack until completely cool.
Yield:
3 loaves.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Put in casserole dish and bake at 225° for 3 1/2 hours, covered.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: oklahoma chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Let chicken marinate for 1 hour.
Drain chicken, saving marinade.
Place chicken, skin side up, over charcoal or in a broiler pan 8 inches from heat. Brush on marinade every 15 minutes.
Broil 20 to 25 minutes on each side or grill until chicken is tender and brown.

title: artichoke-chile dip
directions: Chop the artichoke hearts.
Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, chopped chile peppers, 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into an 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve warm with tortillas, breadsticks or other chips.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix laundry starch, cornstarch and cold water to a smooth paste.
Add Ivory flakes and mix until smooth.
Add the warm water and cook slowly or in double boiler until thick.
Add glycerin (which makes it smoother) and beat with an egg beater.
Divide into jars and add food coloring as desired.

title: onion soup
directions: In saucepan, saute onions and garlic in butter for 7 to 10 minutes until onions are tender, stir constantly.
Add 1/4 cup wine, cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining wine, chicken and beef broths. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, marshmallow creme and ginger.
Mix in orange rind.
Use as a dip for melon, pineapple, berries, bananas, oranges and kiwi.

title: cowboy cake
directions: In saucepan, boil the sugar, hot water, raisins, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and salt for 3 minutes.
Dissolve baking soda in few drops of water and add to saucepan mixture.
Cool.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: healthful oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salty water until tender; drain.
Add mushroom soup, cheese, margarine and milk.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add the chopped eggs and can of tuna.
Pour into greased dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke pizazz
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Combine with rest of ingredients. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers and chips.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Add sugar, butter, Crisco and salt to hot mashed potato. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to potato mixture. Cover bowl and place in lukewarm water.
Let rise until spongy 2 or more hours.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Cover in large bowl and allow to rise in warm place overnight or 5 hours.
Knead light on floured board.
Spread evenly with well buttered fingers on shallow greased pan.
Cover and allow to rise until light.
Make holes for butter, brown sugar and cream.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let stand for at least 5 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Dip your favorite pieces of fruit into this mouth watering delight.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Allow cake to cool. Mix pudding with milk. Spread over cake. Blend whipped topping and cream cheese. Spread over pudding mixture. Spread pineapple over cake. Sprinkle with coconut. Chill.

title: chicken dinner delight
directions: Cook chicken and onion together.
Mix celery, bread, egg and seasoning together.
Debone chicken and line the bottom of the pan with chicken meat, put dressing over chicken.
Dilute soup with 1 can of chicken broth and pour evenly over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until crisp and brown on top.

title: acorn squash with apples
directions: Halve the acorn squash; remove seeds.
Brush with butter and fill with thawed escalloped apples.
Bake in baking dish at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with crumbled Italian sausage.
Serves 4.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onions in drippings until tender.
Stir in flour slowly; blend well.
Add vinegar and water. Cook (stirring) until bubbly and slightly thick.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Crumble bacon.
Carefully stir bacon and potatoes into hot mixture.
Heat through, stirring lightly to coat potatoes.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: herb baked potatoes for microwave
directions: Melt the margarine in microwave dish.
Add the garlic or onion powder and thyme.
Cut the potatoes into wedges and cover with the mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and vent.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in microwave.
Sliced onion can be added on top of potatoes or used instead of one of the potatoes.

title: gum drop diamonds
directions: Toss gum drops in about 1/4 cup of the flour.
Set aside. Beat eggs and water together.
Add brown sugar. Add flour, salt, cinnamon and blend.
Add nuts and floured gum drops. Mix well. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Grease and flour tube pan. Layer pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pouf half of cake batter over this.
Mix
oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Spoon over batter.
Then add remaining batter.

title: zesty slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick butter; set aside.
Cream sugar and remaining butter; add eggs to sugar mixture.
Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Add candy mixture.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ritz crackers snacks
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Lay Ritz crackers side by side on jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour butter/sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Let cool approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on serving tray.

title: baked whole salmon
directions: Rub fish with salt, pepper and lemon.
Wrap in foil.
Bake slowly at 250 - 300° for three hours or until done.
Remove foil. Remove skin.
Place salmon on large platter.
Serve with melted butter and lemon.
Perfect side dishes to accompany the baked salmon are parsleyed new potatoes and green peas with pearl onions.
Lemon meringue pie would make an excellent dessert.

title: christmas banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch pan or 9-inch spring-form pan, reserving 1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
Gradually add creme de menthe to Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs; freeze.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water.
Add sugar, salt and Crisco into a large bowl.
Mix in boiling liquid (cool).
Add egg and yeast mixture. Add 3 cups of flour.
Knead on floured surface until it makes soft elastic dough.
Oil dough and let rise.
Punch down to make into rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° in a greased pan for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: monday night chicken
directions: Use chicken pieces to suit your family's tastes.
In a baking dish, sprinkle chicken pieces with about 1 tablespoon soy sauce for each piece.
Then sprinkle with the lemon pepper marinade and garlic salt.
Broil, bone side up first, for about 20 minutes or until crispy.
Turn and continue broiling for another 20 minutes. Pour extra marinade out of pan, then pour over chicken when you turn it.

title: margie's crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer until warm.
Serve warm with crackers on the side.
Makes 24 servings.

title: friday night pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Roll flat into patties and fry.
Eat a lot!

title: pineapple filling(good with ham)
directions: Mix all together.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(I only use 1 cup sugar and it is just fine.)

title: peanut crescents
directions: Mix
oleo
and butter thoroughly; add beaten egg yolks. Add yeast that has been dissolved in the warm milk.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Knead
well;
roll
out
thin and cut in wedges. Place small
amount
of
Nut Filling on each wedge and roll in crescent shape.

title: mom's lite cheese danish
directions: Heat
oven
Mix
sugar
and cinnamon.
Spray tortillas with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle each tortilla with
scant 1/2 teaspoon sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Turn tortillas over;
repeat
process.
Cut each tortilla into 4 wedges. Stand rounded
edge
of each tortilla wedge in bottom of each muffin cup by curling in sides.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned and crispy.
Cool.

title: fish fillets with dijon sauce(serves four)
directions: Arrange fillets on microwave bacon or roasting rack with thickest portion to the outside.
Overlap thin areas in center of rack.
Combine mayonnaise, Dijon mustard and lemon juice.
Spread over fillets.
Sprinkle with red pepper and chives.
Microwave on High (100% power) for 5 to 8 minutes until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Let stand 1 minute before eating.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut top of cauliflower, not stems.
Add sugar and mayonnaise. Stir well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Mix cream cheese, chicken, onion, margarine, milk, salt and pepper together.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 triangles by pressing perforations together.
Spoon equal portions of chicken mixture into triangles.
Fold corners to center and seal together. If desired, you may sprinkle tops with finely crushed croutons. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Delicious served with broccoli salad.)

title: chewy maple bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add syrup and egg; beat well.
Add flour to creamed mixture; add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in oats and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: In a medium sized saucepan over a medium flame, stir together the hot water, chili powder, tomato sauce, cumin, garlic salt and onion powder.
In a 2 cup or larger measuring cup, mix together about 1/4 cup of flour with some hot water in order to make a semi-thick maltlike mixture.
Add this mixture to the saucepan mixture by using a sieve.
You will pour the flour mixture through a sieve in order to thicken the sauce in the saucepan.
It is very important that you continue stirring the sauce in the saucepan while adding the flour mixture.
You may need to make more of the flour mixture to add to the enchilada sauce until you reach a desired consistency for the sauce.
The sauce should be slightly thick and not too runny.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Line baking dish with Fritos. Add a layer of chicken.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let marinate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: hot dog cheesies
directions: You will need wooden toothpicks.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add enough pineapple juice to make a gallon.
A little sugar can be added if you wish.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.
Firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
In saucepan, combine remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat through and serve with meat loaf.

title: maxine's hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Roll out thinner.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Top with mixture of first 3 ingredients, then top with veggies.
Cut into squares.

title: beef, tomato and lima bean soup
directions: In Dutch oven, in hot oil, brown beef well.
Push to one side. Add onions and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Add salt, oregano, pepper, bay leaf, 3 cups water, tomatoes and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add more water, if necessary.
Add lima beans.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until all is tender.
Remove meat; cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Add to soup with any bone marrow.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole with oleo.
Cook chicken, bone and devein.
Cook noodles and peas as directed.
Layer chicken, then noodles, then the peas.
Ladle the peas out of their water with a slotted spoon.
Use the broth that you cooked the chicken in to make your gravy.
I use some of the broth to make the filling with.
Pour the gravy over everything and top with the filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood marinara con linguine
directions: In deep frying pan combine oil, onions and garlic; saute slowly until soft.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook about 10 minutes on medium heat.
Add shrimp, scallops, wine, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, on medium heat about 10 minutes.
Prepare linguine according to box directions; drain and top with sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: cheesy pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and cheese to make a soft ball.
Roll out to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut in strips.
Twist strips in pretzel shapes.

title: dump cake i
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with a spoon and put into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together jello and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: chutney sausage balls
directions: Roll sausage into bite-size balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Drain. Keep warm in a doubler boiler. Combine chutney and sour cream; heat thoroughly. Pour over sausage balls. Serve in chafing dish with wooden picks.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Beat the oleo and Crisco until fluffy. Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Put milk in cup, then add water to make 1 cup.
Add milk and flour, a little at a time. Fold in nuts. Add cherries. Grease and flour pan (Bundt).
Put in cold oven.
Turn on to 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't open oven for at least 2 hours.
Do not use self-rising flour.

title: polish kielbasa and potatoes
directions: Using heavy-duty foil, tear off a large piece.
Take cleaned potatoes and make slices almost through them.
Stick a slice of onion in each cut.
In foil, put several pieces of kielbasa with potatoes and onion.
Wrap tightly and grill on barbecue for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Juices from kielbasa will flavor potatoes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar, peanut butter, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla, then oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and confectioners sugar, cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: remaki
directions: Cut chicken livers in half.
Cut water chestnuts in 3 pieces. Pour teriyaki sauce over livers and water chestnuts in a bowl. Refrigerate for 4 hours, then drain.
Cut bacon slices in half and wrap livers along with a piece of the water chestnut.
Secure with a wooden toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Set oven on broil for 550°, turning occasionally, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cover and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: rosemarie's oriental chicken salad
directions: Night before, marinate in zipper bag as long as possible (try to marinate at least 2 hours or all day (night). Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: tostados
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Shred cheese, lettuce and dice tomatoes; set aside.
Heat refried beans in saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup cheese to beans.
Heat tostado shells at 350° just until hot.
Add refried beans, hamburger, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce to top of tostado shell.
Garnish with sour cream, if desired.

title: professional cake icing
directions: Beat with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Store in covered container or frost cooled cake.
For decorating: use only 1/3 cup Crisco (cake decorating bag).

title: pickled peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Put vinegar, sugar and water in saucepan and boil 1 minute.
Place peppers in hot solution just to heat.
Put garlic and salt in pint jars and cover peppers with hot vinegar solution.

title: holiday potato bake
directions: If potatoes are not seasoned, salt and pepper to taste.
In a bowl, lightly beat egg yolks.
Add melted butter and paprika, beating well. Combine mixture with potatoes, cheese and chopped peppers.
Stir until well blended. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Spoon into buttered 6-cup ring or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and cook slow (325°) for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Take juices and Cokes and heat; add Jell-O and dissolve.
Remove from heat; cool and add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.

title: vanilla icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thickened. Cool and add remaining ingredients. Beat until fluffy.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and beat with fork.
Add pineapple.
Pour in a greased casserole; sprinkle bread cubes on top and pour butter over all the bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hugh donald's whiskey sour punch
directions: Mix the ingredients in a gallon or bigger punch bowl.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat dry cake mix, brown sugar and peanut butter in large bowl on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of the crumbly mixture.
Beat the remaining crumbly mixture, water, oil and eggs on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour batter into pan.
Stir nuts into reserved crumbly mixture and sprinkle over batter.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tender chicken and broccoli
directions: Pound chicken breasts to thin slices. If the breasts are thick, use a knife to fillet them first and then pound them.
Dip flattened chicken in flour.
Heat oil in pan and brown the chicken breasts lightly.
In a deep pan on top of stove, add 1 can chicken broth and 1 package onion soup mix. Add chicken and simmer. Add the broccoli spears.
Cover and cook until done. Serve over rice.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Mix with 2 3/4 cups scalding milk, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato baked bass
directions: Prepare the rice according to package directions.
The rice should be fully prepared before the fish is baked.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place shortening and sugar in a bowl.
Mix together well.
Add eggs and mix together. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in separate bowl.
Stir and add half of the flour mixture and half of the mashed bananas.
Mix for 30 seconds, then add remaining flour and banana mixture.
Mix an additional 30 seconds. Stop and scrape bowl. Blend walnuts into mixture, about 15 seconds.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: coffee cake exceptionale
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan, 10 x 4-inches, 12 cup Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
In large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Mix in flour, baking powder, soda and salt alternately with sour cream.
For tube or Bundt pan spread 1/3 of batter (about 2 cups) in pan and sprinkle with 1/3 of Filling (about 6 tablespoons).
Repeat twice.
For loaf pans, spread 1/4 of batter (about 1 1/2 cups) in each pan and sprinkle each with 1/4 of Filling (about 5 tablespoons).
Repeat.
Bake about 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly in pan(s) before removing.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.
If using self-rising flour, omit baking soda, and salt.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix first 3
ingredients together thoroughly; pour into freezer bucket.
Use electric
or hand turned ice cream freezer; add ice and rock salt alternately.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish, tightly covered.
Bake at 350° until rice is done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mustard 'n' cheddar pretzel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine hot roll mix, yeast packet, mustard and cheese. Add water, 1 egg and butter, stirring until blended. Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes or until smooth. Cover and let rest 5 minutes. Cut dough into 18 pieces. Roll each piece of dough on a lightly floured surface into a 14-inch rope. Twist into a pretzel shape. Place on lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with remaining egg and sprinkle with kosher salt. Bake at 400° for 14 minutes or until golden. Serve warm. Makes 18 rolls.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Bring vinegar to boil.
Add seasonings.
Pour into glass jar. Drop in eggs.
Cover and let stand at least 10 days before serving.

title: seashells in the sunset
directions: Cook macaroni until el dente.
Saute onion in 1/4 c. butter and add flour.
Add milk and continue to stir until mixture comes to a slow boil and thickens.
Season with pepper.
Add cheese, salmon and parsley.
Add macaroni and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 2 Tbsp. butter, toss with breadcrumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart pan.
Heat slowly.
Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients.
Add the vinegar.
Cook to light crack (268°).
Remove from heat.
Add the butter; sift in the baking soda.
Stir.
Turn out (do not scrape) onto battered pan.
Turn edges to center to cool.
When warm to the touch, pull to a light taffy color.
Pull into long strips; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Use cornstarch to keep from sticking to fingers.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken gravy
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and remove lumps.
Add milk gradually to thick milk gravy.
Add vegetables and chicken. Simmer until hot.
Add more milk if gravy is too thick.
Pour over biscuits.

title: chili chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all the ingredients together. Place in a large casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes.
This can be prepared, frozen and reheated.
Yield:
6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: party polenta
directions: Saute beef and onions in deep saucepan; stir occasionally until beef is browned.
Drain off fat.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, salt and hot sauce.
Prepare muffin mix as package directs.
Spread over top of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: el gondo
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add tomatoes and chili mix, then simmer for about 15 minutes.
Layer in a large pan the yellow rice, hamburger mixture and crushed chips; repeat.
Warm soup with 1/2 can water; pour over top.
Bake for 15 to 30 minutes at 350° or until warm.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon on a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ham-asparagus rolls
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan, blend in flour, salt and milk; cook until thickened.
Add Swiss cheese and stir until melted. Combine cooked rice with this mixture.
Remove 1 cup sauce mixture to separate container.
Put 1 tablespoon or so on narrow end of ham slice quarters.
Top this with several asparagus spears.
Roll ham around spears.
Place in 2-quart greased casserole dish, edge side down.
Pour remaining sauce over.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and chicken.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add water; cover.
Let simmer slowly until tender. Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well. Add dumplings.
Arrange chicken on top.
Heat through and serve. For more gravy, add 1/2 pint sweet cream to sour cream.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add butter, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add blueberries.
Put in greased muffin tins or use muffin liners. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except salmon and bread crumbs.
Blend in salmon and bread crumbs.
Bake in greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with lemon wedge.
Serve with creamy white sauce and peas.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Keep in airtight container until ready to use.
Put 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in cup; mix with hot water.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt and mushrooms, cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Before serving, stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles or rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or tomato soup

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry; prick each potato with a fork several times.
Place potatoes on paper towels in microwave. Microwave at High, 20 or 30 minutes, turning potatoes after 10 minutes.
Remove potatoes when they feel soft and cut down the middle with knife.
Carefully remove all the insides, leaving the peeling intact.
Mix potatoes, margarine, mayonnaise and milk together with mixer until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Spoon mixture back into potato shells and top with grated cheese. Return to microwave and cook for about 1 minute until cheese is melted.
Serve with any type of meat.

title: christmas cheer dessert
directions: Mix all together with mixer and refreeze.

title: no bake caramel squares
directions: Mix brown sugar, egg, butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add coconut, pecans, vanilla and 3/4 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and spread on half of crackers, then top with crackers.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick sauteed summer squash
directions: Wash and slice squash vertically, then set aside.
Melt margarine on low heat in skillet.
Add onion and simmer until soft.
Place squash in skillet with onion.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and sugar.
Saute over low heat, then cover and simmer until tender.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake as your crust.
Mix dressing mix, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat until consistency is smooth. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in butter or margarine.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add mushroom, onion and celery mixture.
Add salt and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Serve hot with Fritos or chips.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Mix pecans and coconut.
Put in bottom of long 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cake mix over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: In a large bowl, mix ingredients with your hands.
(Keep a bowl of water beside you to keep fingers wet while mixing.
You can add shredded Cheddar cheese to mixture, if you like.)

title: infallible pound cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour; stir well. Then
add
flavorings.
Bake
in
a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel salad
directions: Pour pineapple and fruit cocktail into a colander.
Set aside to drain.
Cream 1/2 cup milk, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together and set aside.
Mix Dream Whip and remaining milk until fluffy.
Mix Dream Whip mixture with cream cheese mixture.
Add the canned fruit and pecans to the cream cheese mixture.
Blend everything together well.
Sprinkle a few pecans on top of salad. Refrigerate overnight.

title: light'n lemony cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk and add lemonade.
Then add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature to softened a bit before cutting and serving. Store leftover pie in freezer.
Recipe can be doubled.
Can use frozen orange juice in place of lemonade.
Can use light cream cheese.

title: passion fruit-pineapple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spray a jelly roll pan with nonstick spray.
Spread the dough on pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Mix cream cheese and salad dressing mix.
Add mayonnaise in mixer until well blended.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese, in order given.
Cut and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water or milk.
Add sugar and salt. Beat egg slightly.
Melt margarine. Mix both into milk mixture. Add flour to mixture until it won't beat anymore.
Knead in remaining flour.
Put in greased bowl, cover and put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Shape into any type of roll. Let rise to double.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or lightly browned.

title: mrs. goodman's chocolate rum angel
directions: Blend first four ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring, until mixture is of custard consistency and coats a spoon, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to hot custard, stirring to dissolve.
Remove 1 cup of custard and add to chocolate chips. Stir until chocolate is melted.
Set aside.

title: bananas and peanuts
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, vinegar and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add butter or oleo and mix well.
Put the pan right into the refrigerator and cool.
When ready to serve, slice each banana into half, then each half into a half.
Place these quarters into a flat dish, cut side up; pour cooked dressing over them and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: 60 minute never fail yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour it over the salt, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
While the milk mixture is cooling, put the yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Add water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Add the cooled milk mixture to the yeast mixture.
Stir in 1 cup flour at a time.
Cover bowl.
Let rise 15 minutes in a warm place. Put dough on floured board and knead about 20 times.
Make into rolls or balls.
Cover.
Let rise again 15 minutes in a warm place. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stores well.

title: original coney island sauce
directions: Chop onions real fine and brown with hamburger.
After brown, add all ingredients except hot dogs.
Grind hot dogs and add to mixture.
Cook until it thickens.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together using enough milk to make a moist or thick batter.
Drop in hot, deep oil.
Cook until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Allow it to get firm.

title: bran bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a greased baking pan.
Bake one hour in a slow oven.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Put yeast and water in a bowl for a few minutes; then add buttermilk and oil.
Then add dry ingredients.
Roll out, cut and bake at 400° for abut 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cream cheese wafers
directions: Mix and pour over wafers. Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Cool and top with topping.

title: ravishing rice
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until golden brown.
In saucepan, cook soup and rice in water for 7 minutes. Combine all ingredients and garnish with parsley or almonds.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in shallow pan.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and onion salt.
Pour over Chex and nut mixture until evenly coated.
Bake in shallow dish (like a cookie sheet) for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Mix together eggs, sugar and flour (beat as little as possible).
Combine the two mixtures again stirring very little.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and cheese in hot water. Pour liquid over Jell-O, then add pineapple juice. When Jell-O begins to congeal, fold in pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts. Mold in rectangular 8 x 12-inch dish. Yield: 12 servings.

title: indian pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix cornmeal and salt.
Combine with cold milk; mix well.
Add hot milk and cook until thickened (5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Beat eggs, then blend in a small amount of cooked mixture.
Stir into rest of mixture and add shortening.

title: spinach dip
directions: Melt margarine; add onion and cook until clear.
Add spinach. Stir in soup and seasonings.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with layer of cheese, then mushrooms and almonds.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Stir well; refrigerate when cool.
Reheat for party.
Serve with Melba rounds.

title: granny berthie's original meal gravy
directions: In skillet, heat bacon grease and add 3 of the 7 tablespoons of corn meal and brown.
Put milk in medium size bowl.
Add remaining 4 tablespoons corn meal to milk.
Pour in skillet and stir until well mixed and brought to bubbly boil.
Salt to taste.
Best with cornbread on the side.

title: chicken stove top casserole
directions: Boil chicken thighs, reserving 2 cups of broth.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Put in a bowl.
Put stuffing mix into bowl with chicken.
Add butter and broth, and remaining ingredient, stirring well.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Garnish with poultry seasoning and Old Bay seasoning.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse kraut until brine is gone.
Let drain 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add kraut and mix well.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together in gallon container meant for freezing.
Freeze for 2 days.
Stir several times over the two day period.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water according to package directions.
Add oregano to spaghetti sauce.
(May also add meat and/or mushrooms, if desired.)
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, arrange in layers in the following order:
noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat. Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add milk and cream; mix.
Add fruit, if desired.

title: spicy gazpacho(no fat, low sodium)
directions: In blender, pour entire contents of 1 can of tomatoes and only juice from the second can. Dice tomatoes from second can and set aside. Add onion, bell pepper, cucumber, garlic, onion powder, hot sauce and black pepper. Blend until pureed.
Pour mixture into large bowl.
Add diced tomatoes and mix well. Chill well.

title: evelyn's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; remove skin and debone. Dice chicken and chop eggs.
Drain relish to remove excess liquid. Add pickles to chicken and eggs.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Add sugar to taste.

title: yellow cake
directions: Sift into bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Measure the milk.
Add flavoring to milk.
Add to the bowl 1/2 of the milk, shortening and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add the remainder of the milk and beat 1 minute more.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Combine jellos with 2 cups of boiling water; add 1 cup of cold water and drained crushed pineapple.
Reserve the juice from the pineapple.
Cover the jello mixture with the marshmallows.
Chill until set.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, eggs and 2 cups of pineapple juice; cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool and spread over jello.
Whip cream cheese and Cool Whip together; spread this over cooked mixture and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with crushed Ritz crackers and butter. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: golden waffles(these are wonderful)
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor and blend 1 minute.
Cook on waffle iron sprayed with nonstick cooking spray according to waffle iron directions.
Recipe makes 6 large waffles.
Ultra low-fat.

title: macaroni, sausage and tomatoes
directions: Brown Polish sausage with onion.
Add can of tomatoes and pepper.
Then add to macaroni and cook together for 1/2 hour. Serve hot with bread and butter.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vegetable oil together.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add zucchini, raisins, nuts, vanilla and nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.

title: bubbly cake
directions: Fourth each biscuit.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a Ziploc bag, place sugar and cinnamon.
Shake biscuit pieces in bag and layer in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar. Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes; turn onto plate as soon as you take out of oven.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in airtight container.
Mix will keep for 2 to 4 months in the cupboard.
Yields 6 cups or 48 ounces.

title: best yet slaw
directions: In a small saucepan combine mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Stir frequently over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool in large bowl.
Toss together vegetables.
Add bacon crumbs and mix well.
Pour cool dressing over vegetables and mix.
Serve chilled.

title: lo-cal salad dressing or veggie dip
directions: Put all ingredients into small bowl and beat.
(May increase amounts for larger crowd.)

title: chip dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add enough milk to soften.
Add about a tablespoon ketchup; add "sauce" to your desired taste.
Start with about a tablespoon until you are familiar with the taste you want.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish:
layer of lettuce (torn in pieces), chopped celery, green pepper, purple onion and drained peas.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Cook in microwave approximately 12 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes with a whisk.
When it thickens, add vanilla and oleo.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Make at least 3 layers.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add melted chocolate and eggs. Mix well. Sift flour with soda and add alternately with Coke. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: camping and traveling salad
directions: Drain all vegetables except Chinese vegetables and mix together.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add next 3 ingredients. Pour batter into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with all the butter while hot.
Arrange toast in a buttered baking pan (10 1/2 x 6 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch). Sprinkle with raisins.
Stir salt and all but 2 tablespoons of sugar into the eggs.
Add milk and stir to mix well.
Pour over the toast and let stand 10 minutes.
Press toast lightly down onto milk occasionally so it soaks up most of the milk mixture.
Mix cinnamon with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar and sprinkle over top. Place dish directly on oven rack.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is an appetizing brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter and olive oil until soft, but not browned.
Add diced tomatoes and seasonings; bring to boil.
Simmer, stirring, until tomatoes give off their liquid and mixture begins to thicken, about 6 minutes.
Stir in the corn. Partially cover the pan; lower the heat and simmer gently until lightly thickened, about 15 minutes.
If mixture becomes too thick, add a little tomato juice or water.
Remove from heat; add pepper and serve.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put butter in a baking dish and melt.
Take out 2/3 cup and save for top.
Pour chicken mixture into baking dish.
Spread stuffing on top and bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 1/2 to 1 hour or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all cheese at room temperature.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into a ball after blending and then roll in pecans and dry onion party dip mix.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until brown; set aside.
Combine cream cheese
and
Eagle
Brand
milk; mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer
of cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Heat caramel in microwave;
drizzle on top of creamed cheese mixture.
Sprinkle coconut and pecan mixture on top. Repeat. Serve frozen.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rhubarb blueberry jam
directions: In a large kettle, combine rhubarb and water.
Cook over medium-high heat for 4 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Stir in pie filling.
Remove from the heat; cool for 10 minutes.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process for 15 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yield:
about 8 half pints.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape in 3 rolls and wrap in foil (shiny side in).
Punch holes in bottom of foil and sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake with hole side down on broiler pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Fat runs out holes.
Remove foil, cool on rack, rewrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: quick clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients except half and half in saucepan.
Heat almost to boil but do not boil.
Remove from heat and stir in half and half.

title: rigatoni with vodka sauce
directions: In a large skillet (medium heat), cook onion and margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and vodka.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend in cream and heat to boiling.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Pour over cooked rigatoni.

title: breakfast casserole (sausage)
directions: In a skillet, brown and crumble sausage; drain and set aside. In a large bowl, beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard. Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: black and white bean salad(yields 4 servings)
directions: Rinse beans in cold water and drain.
Toss all ingredients together.
Chill and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: pumpkin pecan cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecan halves, and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Place pecan halves in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Secure each nut to pan with a small dab of butter.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Invert and cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle favorite frosting over top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar (honey) salt and spice.
Add pumpkin.
Mix and stir in milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° about 40 minutes.

title: creamy hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order listed, stirring well after each addition.
Bake in a buttered 10 x 13 dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on the top the last 10 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place 9 French bread slices in single layer in the bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish and top with cream cheese. Place remaining French bread slices on top of cream cheese. Whisk together eggs and the next three ingredients; pour over bread. Cover and chill for 8 hours. Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, shielding with aluminum foil after 20 minutes to prevent excessive browning. Yield: 8 servings.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until all ingredients are dissolved, then add 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup coconut.
Pour evenly into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, cocoa, soda and salt in a small bowl.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter chips.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagne(serves 8)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook onion, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer on low, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Add 3/4 Mozzarella cheese and stir until smooth.

title: sweet potato-marshmallow casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes	and
peel;
mash
or rice.
Add butter, milk, salt and spices.
