Place mixture in a buttered casserole. Push marshmallows
down into the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until marshmallows are brown.

title: mama mary's pineapple cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and lightly floured cake pans.
Bake according to package directions.
Remove from pans and cool on rack while making the pineapple icing.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt the 6 tablespoons of margarine and combine with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together in mixing bowl 2 cups powdered sugar, 1 stick margarine (softened), 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until pudding like and then pour over graham cracker crust.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water.
Let cucumbers stand 24 hours in lime water.
Drain, rinse and let stand 3 hours in clear water.
Drain again.
Let stand overnight in vinegar, salt, spices and sugar. Next morning, bring to a boil; boil slowly for 30 minutes or until clear.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: sweet and sour pork(leftovers)
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add butter and onion; brown.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple liquid; add to pork.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add pineapple and green pepper; cook about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Boil the butter, sugar, milk and cinnamon until syrup is desired consistency (not too thick).
Add vanilla to boiled mixture and pour mixture into a pan.
Dip 2 cans of biscuits into the mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds from cukes.
Cut all vegetables in small chunks.
Cover all with salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook slowly until vegetables are tender and transparent.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: grandma stacey's green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add mayonnaise and evaporated milk slowly, mixing well.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it begins to boil, stop stirring and boil for 1 minute exactly.
Remove from heat. Stir in the rest of ingredients immediately.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper; let dry.
May add coconut in place of peanut butter.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda in bowl. Melt margarine in saucepan. Add water and cocoa. Bring to rapid boil. Pour over flour mixture and blend. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Pour in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° for 5 more minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add baking soda, garlic, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat.
Add the water, milk powder and margarine.
Heat through, but not to a boil.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: coconut apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine apple slices, caramel topping and flour in bowl.
Spoon into deep baking dish.
Peel apart each biscuit into 2 thinner biscuits; place on top of apples.
Drizzle butter over biscuits.
Combine sugar and coconut; sprinkle over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry the onion and meat together.
Boil the other ingredients together.
Add the hamburger mixture for 10 minutes.
Serve between hamburger rolls.

title: cheerios treats(microwave)
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan.
Microwave margarine or spread in large microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted. Add marshmallows.
Toss until coated.

title: candy graham cookies
directions: Melt oleo, butter and sugar slowly over medium heat.
Cook 1 minute after boiling.
Split graham crackers in two and place on foil lined cookie sheets.
Fill tightly with crackers.
Pour mixture over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cook 10 minutes at 350°.
Don't overcook.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: old-fashioned cherry cobbler
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients into a batter.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Pour sweetened cherry mix over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Dough will rise through cherries, causing a sauce effect on the bottom.)

title: spicy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine cake mix, oats, eggs and oil in large bowl; beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: crustless sugar-free cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy like butter. Spray glass pie dish with Pam. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot and yogurt salad
directions: Toss all together and chill overnight.
Before serving, drizzle 6 tablespoons yogurt over all.

title: fluffy white icing
directions: Mix sugar and water; boil, covered, until mixture spins 8 inch thread (242°).
Pour hot syrup slowly into egg whites with cream of tartar added when whites are frothy.
Beat constantly with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture is fluffy and will hold shape.
Icing for 2 layer cake.

title: golden glow salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to pineapple to make 1 cup.
Add salt if desired.
Stir into jello. Chill until slightly set.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Pour into an oiled 4-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper; coat chicken.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook chicken in oil until light brown on all sides, 10 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover tightly and simmer, turning once or twice, about 35 minutes longer.

title: rhubarb lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and stir in egg, lemon rind, juice and water; cook over boiling water until slightly thickened.
Pour over rhubarb and top with a lattice crust.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes then reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: my mom's yummy carrot cake
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar,
soda,
cinnamon, salt and oil. Then beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Beat in the carrots and vanilla. Pour
into 2 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for
30 minutes. When cool, frost with icing prepared as follows.

title: brine for pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Mix with squash, onions and peppers and cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Pack in sterilized pint jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt the semi-sweet chocolate and 14 ounces of the white chocolate.
This can be done in a double boiler or the microwave. If you use the microwave, do it at 30 second intervals and then stir to determine if it is completely melted.
Add the cereal, peanuts and marshmallows to the melted chocolate.
Spread this mixture on a waxed paper-lined pizza pan.
Arrange the cherries on the top, then sprinkle the coconut over the entire pizza.
Melt the last 2 ounces of white chocolate with oil and drizzle over the pizza, giving it the melted cheese effect.
Refrigerate at least overnight, then cut in pizza slices or as desired.

title: cajun sausage spaghetti
directions: Combine mushrooms, carrot, garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in a Dutch oven with vegetable oil and saute for a few minutes.
Add sausage.
Cook until it loses its redness.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, blend in water (and wine), sugar and herb seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes. Serve over hot spaghetti al dente.
Serves 4 to 6.
(Good for ground beef, chicken or shrimp.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Mix shortening with eggs and add to dry ingredients with raw carrot. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with orange icing.

title: so easy sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add 1/3 of the flour.
Mix and add 1/3 more and mix again.
Add rest of flour and mix.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix the milk, pudding and cool whip together.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly on stovetop.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: Pour water into a 4-quart saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add walnuts and allow to return to a boil.
Cook 1 minute and drain. Rinse walnuts under hot water; drain well.
Combine warm walnuts and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Heat 1-inch of oil to 350°.
Fry walnuts in oil for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cool. Store walnuts in a tightly covered container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan, add brown sugar and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt, add to saucepan mixture; mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Prepare red and green jello using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each package.
Chill each flavor separately until set; cut into small cubes.
Blend pineapple juice and 1/2 cup water and bring to boil.
Add lemon jello, stirring to dissolve.
Chill to egg white consistency.
Fold into the lemon jello the Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and red and green jello cubes.
Pour into large dish; chill until set.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk with lemon juice.
Stir until thickened. Stir in almond extract.
Fold in berries and whipped cream.
Pour mixture into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours.

title: orange marmalade muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine egg, 1/4 cup brown sugar, orange juice and oil.
Beat in Bisquick or muffin mix.
Stir in the marmalade and nuts.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Mix final 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on muffins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cook (simmer) 1/2 hour, stirring often.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: german-style red cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves, cut cabbage in quarters, core and grate into skillet.
Slice the apples; add to cabbage.
Add fat, salt and pepper; bring to a boil with just enough water to cover. Reduce heat to simmer until tender, 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving the liquid.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops.
Season to taste.
Add instant rice, pineapple (including juice) and water.
Stir, making sure some of the rice mixture is underneath the pork chops.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stir-fry vegetables and chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
In wok or iron frying pan, cook vegetables in 1 to 2 tablespoons of olive oil until crisp and tender.
Mix all veggies together in dish.
Add chopped chicken.
Salt to taste.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with soy sauce.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: ranchero casserole
directions: Saute onion in
oleo.
Combine
with
cup of cheese, chili, beans, Mexicorn
and
Fritos.
Bake about 15 minutes on 350°.
Mix the reserved cup of Fritos and 1 cup grated cheese. Put on top of casserole
and
put
back
in oven until cheese melts.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 3 rolls on foil and wrap. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Open up foil and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour into 4 thin layer pans. Cook as directed. Mix sugar, powdered sugar, cream cheese and whipped topping. Put filling between layers and spread with pie filling.

title: shrimp cocktail crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon of margarine, horseradish, catsup, lemon juice and shrimp.
Mix well. Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half to make 16 triangles.
Place a rounded teaspoonful of the shrimp mixture on the center of each triangle.
Fold short ends of each triangle over filling.
Fold long end over all.
Brush each with margarine. Sprinkle with cheese and sesame seed.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: herb bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In large bowl stir together first 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, stir together milk, oil and egg.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 minutes, or until done.
Immediately remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack at least 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine soup, margarine, salt, pepper, onion, and cheese. Gently mix in the potatoes and pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Roll into balls and then in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove and press candy kiss or chocolate star on top.

title: spinach puff
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, adding onion to the pan as spinach cooks.
Drain well.
Fold in the eggs and sour cream.
Blend in the Parmesan cheese and flour.
Stir in the butter, nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: no fry doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl constantly. Stir in remaining flour until smooth. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double (50 to 60 minutes).
Turn dough on well floured surface; dough will be soft.
Roll out. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Brush with butter.
Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Shake in bags of granulated, powdered or cinnamon sugar.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: pink angel dessert
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in small saucepan.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in sugar.
Heat to dissolve gelatin and sugar. Add frozen lemonade.
Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Pour into large mixer bowl.
Slowly beat in evaporated milk.
Continue to beat until mixture is light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Fold in cake cubes.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and garlic powder.
Fry bacon.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Drain kidney and pinto beans.
In large casserole dish, combine all beans and sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Make into 1-inch balls.
Fry or bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Simmer in sauce at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute meat, onions and green pepper in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles or rice. Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Additional broth may be added, if necessary, during cooking.
Salt to taste.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: hot sausage and sauce
directions: In saucepan mix chili sauce and grape jelly.
Stir until smooth.
Fry sausage in pan.
Cut into chunks and add to sauce. Simmer in sauce for 2 minutes and serve.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add soup, water and milk. Bring to boiling point.
Add crabmeat and spices.
Cook 3 more minutes.

title: susie's cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed. Pour 3/4 cake mix in 13-inch baking pan (rest of cake mix not needed).
Cook cake and let cool.
Punch holes in top of cooled cake with a fork.
Pour undrained can of pineapple over cake.
Make instant pudding with directions on box. Pour pudding on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Yum!

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in pineapple.
Combine flour and soda; stir into mixture.
Bake in pan for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Drain 1/4 cup liquid from tomatoes.
Blend cornstarch and seasonings with liquid.
Combine with tomatoes and remaining liquid.
Toss bread crumbs with melted butter.
Mix half with tomatoes.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole; top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parmesan baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine flour, onion powder, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Dredge fillets in mixture.
Coat a baking dish with nonstick spray.
Place fish in baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over fish, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake approximately 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: cynthia's lemon oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in next four ingredients.
Sift together baking soda, salt and baking powder and mix into preceding.
Mix in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt
butter;
add
cocoa.
Mix with other ingredients, which have already been mixed together.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Soften the cheeses at room temperature for 2 hours.
Place everything except walnuts in a large bowl and whip until blended. Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in walnuts.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until completely chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In a small saucepan, stir brown sugar into water until dissolved.
Bring to a boil and boil gently for 5 minutes (will begin to thicken).
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour cooled caramel syrup over popcorn.
Spray hands with nonstick cooking spray and form into balls.
Makes 8 caramel popcorn balls.
Don't serve popcorn to children under 4, as it poses a choking hazard.

title: candy cookies(chocolate hob nobs no bake cookies)
directions: Mix cocoa, milk, sugar, and margarine. Bring to a boil and let boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and oats. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: kool-aid slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in plastic container in freezer.
Freeze solid.
Set out 1 hour before serving.
When the ingredients come out, it should be in the form of icy slush.

title: pecan rolls, also called heavenly bits
directions: Cream the margarine or butter until fluffy.
Fold in sugar, beating all the while.
Fold in flour. Add vanilla.
Roll in fingers about 1 1/2-inches long and 1/2-inch thick.
Place on cookie sheet and bake slowly for 1 hour at 275° to 300° (according to your oven).
While they are warm, roll in the powdered sugar.

title: mexican french bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spread butter over surface of bread. Mix chiles, cheese and mayonnaise together. Spread over buttered surface of bread. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Cover bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (approximately 10 minutes).
Let cool 10 minutes.
Beat at room temperature the cream cheese, dressing and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on crust.
Scatter vegetables on top.
Cut into squares.
Serve or refrigerate.

title: dark chocolate fudge sauce
directions: In a 1-quart glass bowl, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, cocoa and cream.
Mix well.
Add butter.
Heat well.
Stir in top of double boiler or heat in microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring once, until well mixed and sugars are dissolved. Stir in vanilla and salt.
Serve hot over ice cream, cake or fruits.
Can cool and store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Reheat in microwave on Low for 1 to 2 minutes until of good pouring consistency.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: vegetable-beef-barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Stir in all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables and barley are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: pork chop limas
directions: Soak and cook limas until nearly done (tender).
Salt and brown chops on both sides.
Drain off excess fat.
Drain cooked limas and add to chops.
Cover with onion slices.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over all.
Sprinkle with seeds.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, at least one hour or until chops are tender.

title: oven baked potato
directions: Peel potatoes.
Put oil in shallow bowl.
Mix corn flake crumbs, paprika and salt on wax paper.
Roll potatoes in oil, then in mixture, covering completely.
Grease baking pan, place potatoes in pan and bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the cooked chicken (after bones are removed and chicken has been chopped) with chicken and mushroom soup and mayonnaise.
Put the cooked broccoli into the bottom of casserole dish and pour the chicken mixture over the top.
Grate sharp Cheddar cheese over the top and sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and dates in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in cereal and pecans.
Let cool to touch. Roll into small balls and shake in plastic bag of powdered suger to coat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, molasses, vinegar, water and butter until hard crack in cold water.
Take off heat.
Add the vanilla.
Stir in the soda.
Beat until foamy, then pour over corn and stir.

title: banana salad
directions: Slice bananas and press in bowl.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well; mix remaining ingredients and add to spinach.
Roll into balls the size of meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
The color should be golden brown with some green showing.

title: special tea
directions: Combine water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon in 2-quart saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil.
Add orange juice and tea.
Brew 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: moma's good pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well and mix in flour and buttermilk. Cook on hot griddle or skillet lightly covered by butter or cooking spray.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In large size mixing bowl, blend peanut butter and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
For large cookies, drop by tablespoon about 2-inches apart onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: yum - yums
directions: Sprinkle chips and nuts over batter.
Mix brown sugar and egg white; spread over chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: family favorite sandwiches
directions: Butter bread slices.
Spread each slice with mayonnaise. Spread one slice with peanut butter.
Cover one slice with chopped celery.
Assemble sandwiches and cut into thirds.

title: wood chuck
directions: Make cheese sauce by combining milk, butter, flour and cheese. Do not boil.
Blend well; saute mushrooms and green pepper in small amounts of butter.
Toss all ingredients over warmed Chinese noodles.

title: sweet 'n sour stir-fried beef
directions: Trim excess fat from beef. Cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips. Cut strips across grain into 1/8-inch slices.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies into fine crumbs and line bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Mix milk and instant puddings together. Add vanilla ice cream and mix. Pour over crumbs. Spread with Cool Whip and nuts. Freeze. Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: jelly puffs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place 12 chocolate or vanilla wafers on ungreased baking sheet.
Cut 6 large marshmallows in half.
Place one half, cut side down, on each wafer.
Snip top of each marshmallow.
Bake just until marshmallows are puffed, 5 to 7 minutes.
Place 1/4 teaspoon jelly on each marshmallow.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet; drain.
Add all other ingredients listed.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add 2 cups of shredded cabbage, 1 cup frozen or fresh green beans (optional) and 1/2 cup small elbow macaroni.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when ready to serve in each bowl.

title: devil's food cake(makes three layers or a 9 x 13-inch pan)
directions: Sift together and mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
"Do not beat cake."
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: canned green beans
directions: Put beans in large pot. Cover with water. Add salt, sugar & vinegar. Bring to a boil. Cook until beans turn brown. Ladle into hot sterilized jars using liquid from pot. Seal. Drain and rinse before cooking.

title: sorghum baked beans
directions: Place beans in a large crock; cover with water and soak 8 hours.
Transfer to saucepan and cook until beans begin to simmer and skins burst.
Drain.
Place beans in a baking dish or pan. Mix ingredients and pour over beans, stirring well.
Bake in 300° oven for several hours, until bubbly, but not dry.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, and oil; add eggs. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to sugar mixture. Combine flour and spices; add to sugar mixture. Add 1 c. boiling water; mix well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. While still hot, sprinkle powdered sugar on top. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken and shred. Mix Cheez Whiz, cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, Ro-Tel, salt and pepper together. Place chicken in 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Crush Doritos. Pour over casserole. Bake another 5 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
(For softer, rounded cookies, add 1/4 cup more flour.)
Stir dry ingredients together; blend in.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Cookies should still be soft.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: snappy cheese wafers
directions: Combine cheese and margarine; cream until smooth, using electric mixer.
Add pepper, mustard and flour; mix well.
Stir in rice cereal.
Form dough into small balls; flatten with a fork to make wafers.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
About 3 dozen.

title: fruit supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Add a small amount of drained juice if necessary. Chill and serve in pretty dessert cups. Yields 12 servings.

title: easy soft pretzels
directions: Unroll pizza dough onto an 18-inch piece of lightly floured wax paper.
Roll dough into a 16 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut dough lengthwise into ten 1-inch wide strips.
Shape each strip of dough into circle overlapping about 4 inches from each end and leaving ends free.
Taking one end of the dough in each hand twist at the point where the dough overlaps.
Carefully lift each end across to the edge of the circle opposite it.
Tuck ends under to seal.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Scrub and trim zucchini, then cut into long thin slices. Bring 1-inch water to boil in a large pot.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Cook zucchini about 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: potato casserole
directions: Coarsely shred the potatoes.
Add cheese and melted butter. Mix lightly and add onion, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Dot with butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken delight
directions: Season chicken after it is cut up. Fry until brown. Place chicken in a casserole dish. Put the bread crumbs over the chicken. Put the can of cream of chicken soup and a can of water into a bowl and mix very well. Pour over chicken and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Wash and clean chicken. Put in pot, cover with water.
Boil for 30 to 35 minutes.

Remove from pot, put in colander to cool. Peel and dice potatoes and put in pot with juice from chicken. Add onion powder, salt and pepper. Pick chicken off bone and put in pot with other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheese con queso
directions: In double boiler top over boiling water, melt Velveeta cheese in water and add green chilies, taco sauce, garlic powder and Mexene.
Mixture will be thin so thicken it by adding cornstarch dissolved in cold water by adding it little at a time.
If it gets too thick, add water.
Will separate under refrigeration, but does not matter as reheats in double boiler.
Yields 1 1/2 pints.

title: fried scallops
directions: In a shallow dish, combine flour with salt. Roll scallops in flour mixture.
In another small bowl, dip scallops in egg, mixed with water.
Then coat with bread crumbs.
Drop into hot oil in fryer.
Fry until golden, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: meat enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix in beans.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, into hot Crisco briefly and drain.
Spread beef and bean mixture in each tortilla and roll.
Place in shallow baking dish. Cover with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven at 350° and heat until cheese is melted.
If you wish, when serving, top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: scrapple
directions: Cut sausage into 4 sections. Cook in 2 cups water until well done.
Remove meat and put aside.
Pour liquid into bowl and let grease rise to top.
Skim grease off.
Grind or break up meat into 1 cup reserved liquid.
Bring to boil remaining liquid and enough water to make 2 cups.
Stir constantly and add 1 cup cornmeal. Reduce heat and stir for 5 minutes or until very thick.
Add meat mixture, salt and pepper.
Mix and pour into greased loaf pan. Cool, uncovered, in fridge.
Turn onto plate, slice 1/2-inch thick and fry until crisp.

title: chicken-flavored rice mix(an excellent addition to your favorite main dish)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until evenly distributed. Put about 1 1/3 cups mixture each into three 1-pint airtight containers.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 to 8 months.
Makes about 4 cups of Chicken-Flavored Rice Mix.

title: louisiana seafood bake
directions: Prepare seafood (cook shrimp, etc.).
Saute pepper, onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Place seafood in one layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pepper, onion and garlic mixture over seafood.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients into buttered clear glass dish, putting potatoes on bottom.
Combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream and onion.
Mix together.
Pour over potatoes.
Add corn flakes (crushed) on top, then sprinkle on grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, putting on aluminum foil for first 1/2 hour.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine in pan and boil.
Open biscuits.
Cut into quarters.
Mix balance of sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl with lid.
Put cut up biscuits in bowl and shake well to coat biscuits.
Do not grease tube pan. Sprinkle nuts, raisins, etc. in bottom.
Lay cut up biscuits in tube pan.
Pour half of boiled mixture over biscuits, adding more nuts, etc.
Do same with other 2 cans of biscuits.
Pour balance of boiling mixture over.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Turn out onto plate immediately.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix in bottle by hand cream cheese, garlic powder, horseradish and crabmeat (drained).
Make into a ball or mold.
Spoon over sauce (ketchup and horseradish mixed together) to cover mold.
Keep cold; serve with Wheat Thins.
Excellent appetizer.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Then make 1-inch balls of dough and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or when top starts to crack for chewy cookies.

title: acini de pepe macaroni
directions: Cook the acini de pepe macaroni in salted water.
Rinse and drain.
Drain fruit; set both aside.
Cook pineapple juice with the sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Cook until thick; pour over macaroni.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with banana puree.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 or 60 minutes.
May double recipe and make 2 loaves at one time with success.

title: john's picante sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in order in a large pot.
Cook on medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours.
Pour in jars and seal in boiling water for a few minutes.

title: saturday supper pie
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add the oregano, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add cheese and meat mixture.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Pour pizza sauce over top and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch in medium saucepan. Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter, vanilla and cinnamon.
Cool slightly.
Pour into pie crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Whip cream and 2 teaspoons of sugar in small chilled bowl.
Top each piece of pie with dollop of whipped cream.

title: cream of broccoli & shrimp soup
directions: Melt butter, add seasonings and saute about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink.
Add flour, then slowly add 2 cups milk, stirring to blend on low to medium heat (High heat will cause soup to curdle).
Add cheese and melt.
Add broccoli and more milk if necessary for desired consistency.
Season to taste.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter in deep kettle.
Add remaining ingredients, except cashew nuts.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Add cashew nuts and bake additional 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese in pan over medium heat.
Add soup and onions.
Mix well.
Take off stove, then add rice and broccoli. Mix all together.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hughes' crab imperial
directions: Saute peppers and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Beat egg and mayonnaise together in large bowl.
Stir in vegetables and gently add crabmeat.
Spread into pie plate. Spread a little mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Then broil 3 minutes.

title: 5 minute pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Put eggs in a cup and finish filling with milk.
Add this to the butter and sugar; beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder alternately with milk.
Bake in tube pan in a slow oven.

title: baked prune whip
directions: Remove the pits from the prunes and mash to a pulp.
Add lemon juice, grated peel and 2 tablespoons sugar. Blend well. Add remaining 2 tablespoons sugar to the beaten egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold prune mixture slowly into beaten whites and pile lightly in a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Combine sauce ingredients in pan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper.
Cook under grill or on barbecue until nearly done.
Last 15 minutes, brush with the sauce.
Or can marinate in sauce at least one hour before cooking.

title: artichoke hearts spread
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Heat cream and butter together.
Add salt.
Place hash browns in a thin layer in an oblong baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Pour cream mixture over hash browns; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Add butter.
Fold in blueberries.
Put batter into 12 greased muffin pans or use cupcake papers.
Sprinkle the top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a paper bag and shake well.
Use to coat chicken for baking.

title: granny dolvin's tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening in bowl.
Beat smooth.
Save out 1 cup of flour to use on board to work dough smooth.
Sift remaining 2 cups of flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla to egg mixture to make dough. Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Blend ingredients; pour over drained vegetables.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Measure first six ingredients into medium saucepan. Cook on medium heat, constantly stirring until margarine and brown sugar are melted.
Add spices and continue cooking until well blended.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice lemons paper thin and combine with sugar.
Let stand 2 hours or longer.
Add eggs.
Place in pie shell and cover with crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 375° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in iron skillet.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix.
Put in eggs, cottage cheese and onion and pour butter over mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and wash sauerkraut.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Mix all ingredients and store overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep for a week.

title: grandma esh's lemon sponge pie
directions: Grate the lemon and squeeze out juice.
Combine rind, juice, sugar and flour.
Add milk, melted butter and 2 egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° until top is golden brown and thin knife inserted in middle shows clean (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: crunchy peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar and lemon juice.
Turn into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pie baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine muffin mix and nutmeg.
Cut into butter until like coarse crumbs.
Spoon over peaches.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin, eggs, sugar and salt.
Add evaporated milk, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and ginger; beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix ingredients together.
For better flavor, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla and mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup broken nut meats. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mrs. mooney's rolls
directions: Put in large bowl or pan, yeast, warm water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir all together real good and put flour into this mixture and stir well.
Put enough flour to make firm ball not too hard or too soft, just medium.
Pick up in hands and work real good.
Put cooking oil or some melted butter in bowl and grease hands and put well-greased dough in bowl.
Let rise up real good. Then make into rolls in a pan that you have greased with melted butter or oil.
Pass each roll in this to make nice greased rolls. Put in warm place and let rise.
Put in hot oven that you have heated to 500° before you put rolls in oven.
Set oven back to 400° when you put rolls in oven.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
To test, check center roll with a fork to be sure they are done.
Makes good cinnamon rolls, too.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, half and half, evaporated milk, vanilla and salt.
Smash Butterfinger bars into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add milk to fill line.

title: pizza butter
directions: Soften with fork and put on an English muffin.
Put under a broiler until bubbly.

title: shirley fromm's oyster cracker appetizer
directions: Put crackers in large bowl.
Blend rest of ingredients in blender; pour over crackers.
Toss; let stand about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Store in Ziploc bag.

title: connie's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Heat oil in iron skillet.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add hot oil; stir.
Pour batter into skillet; bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix together and cool.

title: pepper steak roast grilled
directions: Pierce chuck roast on both sides and sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Place in bowl and pour Italian dressing and lemon juice over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Next day, rub meat with 2 tablespoons pepper and cook 2 hours on Webber grill turning every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix in order and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker/chocolate crust.
Place in freezer.
Decorate top with chocolate curls.

title: birria(mexican roast)
directions: Place the brisket in a large roasting pan.
Fill roasting pan with water to half-way level of brisket.
Add spices.
Cook 6 to 8 hours, covered, at 250°.
During last hour, add red chilies.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Excellent spread for crackers.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven at 500°.
Season thawed turkey with salt and pepper, then rub melted butter all over the turkey.
Place on a rack in bottom of large oval roaster.
Pour 1 quart boiling water in bottom of roaster.

title: bread and butter pickles(mustard flavor)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour salt over vegetables.
Cover with ice and newspaper paper; weight down mixture.
Let set for 3 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco.
Mix beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Add to first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight in wax paper before using.
Makes 3 (10-inch) shells.

title: hot spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in covered container.
For each serving, stir 2 teaspoons of mix into 1 cup of boiling water. Makes about 70 servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine the first six ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it starts to thicken.
Remove from heat and add butter or oleo.
Pour over cabbage which has been finely shredded.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal-raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir in raisins and oats and mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan (ungreased).
Bake approximately 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: green beef enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas into hot oil until soft.
Stuff with cooked meat and sauteed onion.
Mix together remaining ingredients and melt over low heat.
Pour over rolled tortillas and cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups and broth.
Add stuffing to melted butter.
Place stuffing over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: my mom's stuffed cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients, using only about 1/3 to 1/2 cup ketchup.
Wrap meat mixture in cabbage leaves.
Lay small cabbage leaves on bottom of pot.
Put 1 quart or so of water to 1/2 to 1 cup ketchup.
Stir together to make sauce.
Cook over stove top until meat is done, about 1 or 1 1/2 hours at most.
Great with mashed potatoes.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar, poppy seed, lemon juice and paprika.
Add oil a little at a time, mixing with a wire whisk.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Store in refrigerator.
Serve over fresh fruit or salads.

title: apple caramel pudding(a favorite family dessert, i named.)
directions: Measure the ingredients into a large mixing bowl.

Stir all together thoroughly, until all the ingredients are well blended. Turn into a 9-inch square pan or casserole and spread evenly. Bake in preheated oven, moderately hot, for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm with cream, whipped cream or a scoop of ice cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in casserole dish.
Place the chicken parts on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a covered dish.

title: b.l.t. salad
directions: Cut 18 center slices from tomatoes; lightly salt.
Arrange in 6 lettuce-lined salad bowls.
Coarsely chop tomato ends.
Toss with mushrooms, bacon, onion, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Spoon over tomato slices.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Add soup and water; mix well.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and broccoli is tender.
Makes a large pot and freezes well.
The recipe is also easy made in 1/2 for 1 or 2 persons.
I add more cheese because I love it.

title: carrot coinsfort morgan, colorado
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour over carrots while hot.
Serve cold.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, sugar (2 tablespoons) and butter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar and put over cooled crust.
Add jello to boiling water, stir in raspberries.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Pour over second layer.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and brown sugar until mixture is fluffy.
Add molasses and eggs, beat well.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with water; mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly; sift powdered sugar over top.
Cut into squares.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: good oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, celery, onion and water in Dutch oven. Cook slowly with the lid on for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add creamy chicken mushroom soup and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted.
Continue cooking slowly until it thickens.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt and sift together; set aside. In another bowl, cream the margarine and oil.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture; mix well.
Now, combine wet and dry ingredients and blend well.
Make balls and press with fingers. Bake on next to top rack of preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes. Sprinkle tea cakes with powdered sugar as soon as they are removed from the oven.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add milk while stirring constantly.
Sprinkle nutmeg over pie after filling crusts.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
You may add 3/4 to 1 cup coconut to recipe for Coconut Custard Pie.
Pie is done when jiggled and center appears firm, but soft.

title: taco dip
directions: Let cream cheese set out to soften.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning with hand mixer.
This is your bottom layer.
On top, use shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and taco cheese.
Dip with taco chips or Doritos.

title: best cheese cake
directions: Combine in a small bowl graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Press firmly over the bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
(Chill briefly before filling.)
Blend together the cream cheese, sugar, flour and orange rind and beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add together the eggs and egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in milk.
Pour into crumb crust.
Bake in hot oven (475°) for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 200° and bake 1 hour longer. Let cake remain in oven until cool (about 1 hour).
Remove from oven; cool completely on wire rack.
Loosen around edge with a knife; release.

title: spicy peach nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, blend all, except nuts and raisins, until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into generously greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until tests clean.
Immediately remove from pan.
Cool completely.
If desired, drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.
Store tightly wrapped in refrigerator.

title: taco pie
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread refried beans in the bottom.
Brown hamburger with taco seasoning mix according to package directions and then spread over refried beans and bake in oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Next, combine mayo, sour cream and Ranch dressing mix and spread over hamburger and beans.
Next layer chiles, onion and black olives.
Pour entire jar of taco sauce over this.
Finally, layer lettuce, tomato and Cheddar cheese.

title: minestrone di oregon soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add carrots, potatoes, other veggies, broth and meat.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Add beans and simmer 15 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine buttermilk and preserves.
Add dry mixture and milk mixture alternately, beating only enough to mix. Stir in nuts.
Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing to cooling rack.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
To melted butter, add sugar and corn syrup.
Stir eggs into mixture.
Add cinnamon.
Put black walnuts in a cloth bag and beat into pulp.
Add walnuts to mixture and add 2 tablespoons boiling water.
Bake in 9-inch pie shell (unbaked) for 50 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Mix together in a bowl, then pour in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: Place apple chunks in a bowl and squeeze lemon juice over them.
Add tuna, celery, nuts and mayonnaise.
Toss and serve.

title: double fudge cookies
directions: Cook Eagle Brand milk, oleo and chocolate chips on low heat in a heavy saucepan until melted and pudding like.
Take off heat and add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake; they are soft like brownies.

title: texas lasagna
directions: Cook pintos according to package directions. Brown ground beef lightly. Add everything together.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with love and kind service.
Fold in several cups of prayer, faith and enthusiasm.
Spread over your daily life and serve with a smile.

title: caramel apples
directions: Melt caramels with water in top of double boiler. Stir frequently until mixture is smooth. Add dash of salt. Stick wooden skewers into blossom end of unpared, crisp apples.

Dip apples in caramel syrup and turn until coated on bottom half of apple. If syrup is too thick, add a few drops of water. At once roll bottoms of coated apples in chopped walnuts. Set on cookie sheet covered with wax paper. Chill until coating is firm.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Place muffins on baking sheet.
Spoon pizza sauce over muffins.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: dump salad
directions: Add jello dry to pineapple and cottage cheese.
Stir.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Line two 10 x 15-inch cookie sheets with wax paper.
Beat two egg whites until stiff; slowly add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Fold in vanilla, 1 package of chocolate tidbits and nuts.
Turn on oven to 350°.
Drop with teaspoon on wax paper. Drop close together as dough will not spread.
All of dough needs to go on the two pans.
Place in oven and turn oven off.
Do not open oven for 24 hours.
Makes 60 cookies.
They freeze well.

title: honeycomb candy
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Mix nuts and cereal in large bowl that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour bark over nuts and cereal; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto Pam sprayed wax paper. Cool.

title: good drop cookie
directions: Cream together the sugars; add eggs and oil.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold into creamed ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased large casserole.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, cornstarch and sugar to a boil.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add the strawberry jello and mix well.

title: apple krisp
directions: Line 9-inch square Pyrex dish with sliced apples. Mix dry ingredients and egg until crumbly. Spread over apples. Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cover beets with mixture and simmer 15 minutes. Seal in clean hot jars.

title: slush of a punch
directions: Sweeten to own taste.
Freeze until slushy.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale over and mix.
You can add food coloring to darken color.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Shred chipped beef in a food mill and set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Form into a ball and then roll in shredded beef.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours prior to serving.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: dream dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and applesauce; mix well and chill until firm.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add cream cheese and mix well. Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Garnish with Chocolate-dipped Strawberries.

title: toasted zucchini snacks
directions: Stir zucchini and salt; let stand 1 hour and drain.
Rinse and drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
Add mayonnaise, yogurt, cheese, onions, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and hot pepper sauce. Spread on bread and bake on baking sheet at 375° for 12 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes about 48 rye bread or 32 French bread snacks.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box. Let cool. Add 2 cans fruit cocktail (drained). Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill and serve.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: In large skillet, melt margarine.
Saute parsley and garlic for 1 minute.
Add clam juice, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and remaining seasonings; mix well.
Add shrimp and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until they turn pink, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove shells while eating.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium bowl, mixing well. Can be used on vegetables for deep frying, onion rings, cauliflower, squash, etc. Also great for fish shrimp or oysters.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients
in
large bowl; add flour, oats, soda and salt.
Add
chocolate
chips
and walnuts last. Bake at 325° for 10 to
minutes
or until lightly browned. Cookie will be chewy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 to 3 pans.
Cream sugars, oil and eggs together.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chinese buddhist hand pork-nappa
directions: Boil 6 cups of water in a large pan.
Separate nappa into leaves.
Put nappa into water until it blanches (1 minute). Remove.
Chop scallions.
Mix with ground pork. Be sure nappas strong side is outside.
Slice lengthwise to remove extra fiber. Cut (slice) top off in middle, about 3 inches down.
Add 1 tablespoon pork near the top.
Gently slice nappas lower half 3 or 4 times.
Enclose pork.
Fasten with toothpick.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, vegetable oil and pork.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir.
Serve.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour the melted butter into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the crumbs over bottom of dish. Then coconut, then chocolate chips, then peanut butter chips. Drizzle the sweetened condensed milk evenly over layers.
Sprinkle the nuts over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until set.
Cut into squares while still warm.
They're yummy, chewy and easy.

title: "a special love recipe"(serves 2)
directions: Prepare with one 15-minute massage--kneading, wrapping and stirring.
Complete by mixing on soft satin sheets until done. Layer with "love."
Top with one breakfast in bed.
Indulge as often as time and calories permit.

title: sinful brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Put 1/2 of mix in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Spread 6 ounces chocolate chips and 1 cup nuts on top.
Mix 1 bag of caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Melt and pour over top. Add rest of cake mix (you will have to drop cake mix with a spoon). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Wash, pare and quarter apples.
Steam until tender.
Combine the flour and tapioca; pat into the bottom and sides of an unbaked pie shell.

title: tasty quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form 1-inch balls and lay on ungreased baking sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Flatten with thumb, fingers, fork, sugared glass bottom or small cookie press if design is desired (ceramic or crockery).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 25 to 30.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place aluminum foil in bottom of casserole pan (making clean up easier).
Place and spread rice in bottom of pan.
Add chicken breasts.
Mix soup and water together and pour on top of chicken. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cinnamon chocaccino
directions: In 1-quart nonstick saucepan over high heat, bring 1 cup water to boil; remove from heat and stir in cocoa mix, coffee and cinnamon.
Transfer to heatproof mug and top with whipped cream.

title: risotto rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour soups over rice.
Stir.
Put margarine on top.
Cover.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Stir when half done and before serving.
Good served with beef or chicken.
Serves 6.

title: new orleans jambalaya
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swiss chocolate squares
directions: Combine water, margarine and 1 1/2 squares unsweetened chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes while stirring.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt, then add cooled chocolate liquid into bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Cream together butter or oil, honey, egg and milk.
Combine and add dry ingredients.
Add crawfish and creamed corn, stirring together until just moistened.
Bake in oiled pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top will crack when done.
Serves six.

title: freezer peanut butter pie
directions: Place graham crackers in plastic bag and with dough roller, crush into fine crumbs.
Measure 1 1/4 cups crumbs.
In mixing bowl, combine the crumbs and granulated sugar.
Stir in butter; toss to thoroughly combine.
Press crumb mixture onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill crust while making filling.

title: taylor's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place one quart fresh strawberries in cooled pastry shell. Crush remaining berries in medium saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch and water, blending well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add margarine and few drops of red food coloring, if desired.
Stir until well-blended.
Strain mixture and cool.

title: greek meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil and flour.
Add salt and pepper to taste and mix well. Take 1 Tbsp at a time and roll in flour, shaping into small balls.
Shake off excess flour and fry in very hot olive oil, over medium flame, for 10 minutes or until brown on all sides.
Transfer to large bowl or platter and keep warm until served. Sprinkle with juice of 1 lemon. Serve hot or cold. Serves 6.

title: steph's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in hot water. Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice and gelatin mixture which has been dissolved over hot water.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and chill.

title: indian rice pudding
directions: To
1 cup of rice, add 2 cups water and 1/2
cup
milk. Cook until
rice is soft and a little mushy.
Add
the
brown sugar
to this and simmer over low flame until all
the
water evaporates. In a small frying pan, melt the butter,
then
add cashews	and raisins; saute until cashews turn
light
brown. Add this mixture to the rice and stir.
Serve warm, so you get the butter taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar, margarine and butter in a large bowl until smooth. Add eggs alternately with flour, stirring after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 325° and bake another 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Cool in pan, then invert on plate.

title: party snack mix
directions: Mix first three ingredients and heat together.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the dry ingredients; stir well.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture. Coat with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Let marinate overnight in sealed container.

title: yummy lemon dessert
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, shortening and sugar. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with egg blended with vinegar and vanilla.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for chocolate chips, paraffin and cherries, until well mixed.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls.
Put on waxed paper to harden.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pickle-roll-em-ups
directions: Spread 1 side of each ham slice with 1 tablespoon cream cheese. Place 1 pickle on edge of each ham slice. Roll ham slice around pickle; press edges to seal. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. You may wish to cut each ham roll up into bite sizes.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into ball.
Chill.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine in an iron skillet.
Stir in flour, sugar and cocoa which have been mixed.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk; stir until thick.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: dirt
directions: Cream the cheese and 10x sugar together; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat pudding and milk until it thickens, then add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.
Crush Oreo cookies very fine.
Line flower pots with aluminum foil.
Starting with Oreo crumbs, layer into flower pots, crumbs, pudding mixture, crumbs, etc., ending with cookie crumbs.
Use a silk flower.
Wrap stem with Saran Wrap and place in flower pot.
It really looks like a flower in a pot of dirt.

title: refried bean dip with bacon
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and drain well. Discard all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Saute the onion 2 to 3 minutes over low heat.
Add the beans and stir several minutes.
Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Add sour cream; stir until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl; crumble the bacon on top and serve.
Delicious with baked potatoes or raw or poached vegetables.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add to remaining milk the 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Fold into mixture.

title: chilled oranges
directions: Peel the oranges; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Sprinkle over oranges.
Put into individual paper
cups.
Makes 24 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover peppers and onions with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil mixture for 5 minutes.
Pour into clean hot jars and seal.

title: grandma oliver's sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and eggs until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with cooking spray. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into dish. Place jalapeno slices on top before baking, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, defrost potatoes in microwave for 5 minutes, then stir.
Stir in sour cream and cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and cover top of potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat in small pieces.
Cover meat with flour lightly. Brown in oil (enough to cover bottom of pan).
Brown onions.
Add water (enough to cover meat).
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 3+ hours.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg until smooth.
Add crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: meatless chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Add carrots and green peppers; saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, crushing with spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes, covered.
Can serve with rice, if desired.
Makes 8 (1 1/2 cups each) servings.

title: creamed ham carolina
directions: Heat soup over hot water; gradually add milk.
Add ham.
Slice eggs; add.
Season with salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Split corn bread; cover with ham mixture.

title: yummy pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut fat from pork chops.
Place chops in an ungreased baking dish.
Mix the soy sauce, catsup and honey in a bowl; pour over the chops.
Cover baking dish with aluminum foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more. Serves 4.

title: kim's monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix with cinnamon and sugar.
Melt butter and pour over biscuits.
Spoon into a Bundt pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Make the cake according to directions on the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Beat with hand mixer, softened cheese, milk and pudding (according to directions on pudding box).
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread drained crushed pineapple on top of pudding mix.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple, then sprinkle coconut on top.
Should be made the day before serving.
Deep covered in refrigerator.

title: fran's homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in skillet on all sides.
Put in kettle, cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add fresh vegetables, also put in bouillon cubes, cook till done.
Add all canned vegetables, cook for 1 hour, then add hominy.
Cook another half hour, break up hominy.
Takes about 4 hours to cook, makes about bushel of soup. Put in canning jars, put lids on and put in hot water bath.
Cook about 40 minutes.
Remove from canner, let cool, remove rings from lids and store until needed.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Boil the raisins in the 2 cups of water slowly for 20 minutes.
Add sugar, margarine and allow mixture to cool.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and cold water.
Sift together the flour and baking soda, add to the raisin mixture and mix together until smooth.
Pour mixture into a greased 10 inch tube pan, bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until just tender. Cool, remove skins and shred.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine in covered kettle.
Cook until almost soft, then remove lid.
Cook faster; this will thicken syrup.

title: spaghetti with zucchini-beef sauce
directions: Brown beef and garlic in skillet. Add next 4 ingredients and cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until well mixed. Add seasonings; cover and simmer 30 minutes. Taste and correct seasoning. Cook spaghetti. Serve sauce over hot spaghetti. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually add milk until blended. Cook over low heat to boil.
Simmer 1 minute at a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour in serving dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and water until berries pop open.
Add sugar, Jell-O, pineapple and pecans.
Let stand overnight in a flat pan or bowl.
Mix together cream cheese, marshmallows and whipping cream.
Let stand overnight.
Whip and spread over the cranberry mixture.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, pepper and onion in a large container.
Heat sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed until hot.
Pour over cucumbers and refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work flour in.
Add vanilla and nuts. Shape into balls and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Divide dough in half.
Stir chocolate into 1/2; roll chocolate dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper to form a 16 x 6-inch rectangle.
Repeat with vanilla dough.
Invert chocolate dough on vanilla dough and peel off paper.
Press gently with rolling pin.
Roll up dough as for jellyroll.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: flounder with spinach and cheese
directions: Line each fillet with spinach leaves and cheese; roll up. Assemble in baking dish with edge on bottom of roll.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Place dots of butter on each.
Pour wine (amount varies per taste) into dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.
(Flaky is too well done; should be just fork-tender.)

title: chocolate lace muffins
directions: Line muffin pan with doilies.
Prepare the microwave brownies according to directions on box.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, peel cucumbers, if desired, leaving a few strips of skin on for color.
Thinly slice cucumbers.
In a large bowl, combine cucumbers and remaining ingredients, tossing to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir occasionally.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain and put into buttered 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter. Add the flour, gradually add milk.
Stir in cheese and simmer until melted.
Pour sauce over squash; sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Even people who don't like squash like this dish!

title: johnny appleseed shake
directions: Place ice cream, apple juice, cinnamon and nutmeg in an electric blender container.
Cover container.
Turn blender on to high speed and blend for about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies, including filling, in food processor until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Meanwhile combine milk with pudding mix, stirring until it thickens.
Fold in whipped topping, then fold in cream cheese mixture.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Boil water with bouillon, onions and potatoes until potatoes are done.
Add chicken broth; cook until it boils.
Pinch Velveeta piece by piece and add slowly to soup.
Use wisp to blend Velveeta into soup.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup water.
Add to soup to thicken.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups biscuit mix, sour cream and butter. Mix well. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup biscuit mix on a flat surface. Divide dough into 36 small balls. Place balls on biscuit mix, roll into a ball using the sprinkled biscuit mix if it is sticky. Place 3 balls in each muffin tin cup that has been greased.

title: chocolate unbaked cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine together 1 full minute. Add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and nuts or coconut.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: charleene's cheese ball
directions: Combine.
Form into a ball.
Roll in parsley, chopped pecans or dried beef (I prefer chopped pecans).

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Fold in cake.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix glaze and strawberries.
Spread over cake.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: chili roast chicken
directions: In a large glass baking dish, mix together, yogurt, cinnamon, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and garlic, then add chicken and coat with marinade.
Cover the dish tightly and marinate in the refrigerator overnight.
Preheat the oven to 500°.
Place chicken skin side up on raised broiler rack and place it in the oven. Immediately reduce the temperature to 350° and roast for about 1/4 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: carrot and celery dressing
directions: Cook the giblets until well done.
Take the broth and cool; mix with the well beaten eggs.
Pour over the dry ingredients to make it moist thoroughly.

title: wedding reception punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add concentrates and pineapple juice; stir until well blended.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Serve from punch bowl with frozen strawberries floating on top.
Makes 5 to 5 1/2 quarts.

title: kevin m's favorite spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with hot water.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
If not ready to put on meat, store in covered container.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Stir until well blended; with floured hands, make 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; do not flatten.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes, until tops are dry and cracked.
When taken out of oven, place a chocolate kiss on top and cool.

title: delicious drizzley dessert
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Stir in other ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Press.
Freeze.
Spread softened 1/2 gallon ice cream.
Sprinkle other 1/2 mixture on top of ice cream.
Return to freezer.

title: hot apple cider in a crock-pot
directions: Tie all spices
in a cheesecloth bag.
Put spices, sugar, salt and apple cider in a saucepan; cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve with twists of orange peel.
Use cinnamon stick as stirrer. Yields 10 servings.

title: easy pizza dough
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Add milk and oil.
Stir until mixture forms a ball.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough ten times. Pat dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Put on pizza sauce and fix-ins and bake on 325° until crust is brown.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage on stove.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour all ingredients into large glass dish.
Add sausage and stir real good.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and refrigerate.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in lemon rind and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely.
Pour Lemon Glaze over bread.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in bowl; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Combine the next 6 ingredients; add to bulghur mixture. Serve with the chopped fresh tomatoes, cucumber and green peppers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and let flavors blend.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar and peanut butter.
Add this mixture to pudding, reserving 1/4 cup of the sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Pour into crust and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining sugar-peanut butter mixture on top.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Arrange rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin (jello). Cover with marshmallows. Prepare cake mix, using 2 eggs and required amount of water. Spread batter over mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put butter in frying pan, add garlic and cubed chicken. Cook until done.
Add green pepper and pineapple.
Mix, add brown sugar and vinegar cook and mix until sugar melts.
Add soy to taste. Mix 2 T. corn starch and water until liquid.
Pour into frying pan stirring until mixture has a thickened sauce.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy crab cakes
directions: Tear bread into crumbs and add to crabmeat.
Add Old Bay, red pepper, black pepper and parsley.
